text:
as we close out this last week of youth dating violence awareness month, i want to remind you to not enter relationships because of outside appearance.
-
don’t make the idea of a relationship or marriage an idol where you sacrifice who you are, your friendships and the connections with your family just to have it.
-
recognize that you have to be whole and you mustn’t stay with anyone who doesn’t honor or respect you.
-
love is amazing but love is not attached to sadness and pain.
-
love shows good things so if it’s not good, let go and walk in loving yourself.
-
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
let’s start sharing soul stories! many people don’t know that i went to college to be a journalist. what intrigued me the most about this job is that i would have the chance dive deep into the soul of my subjects. i would be able to understand who they are on a deeper level. i would have opportunities to hear incredible stories of strength, resilience, loss and love. but the most intriguing part was that i would have the opportunity to share those stories with the world.
✨
while i never went on to be become a journalist after college, i am thrilled with the fact that this dream has come full circle for me! with the creation of her soul story, i now have the opportunity to help share the stories i have always wanted to. i am so grateful for this.
✨
and so, if you have a soul story that you would like to share, please let us know! we have a blog, podcast, speaking opportunities, and even more ways to help you do it! our mission is to share as many soul stories as we can, and it starts with yours! let’s get sharing, because through sharing our stories we create a deeper understanding and fuller connection with one another. ✨
xoxoxo,
nicole

text: so proud of @alaynajennings film “unremedied”! the project won #audiencechoice and honorable mention for choreography at the @utdancefilmfest this film is currently circling film festivals- not sure when you’ll be able to watch the whole thing- but i’ll let you know. it is a strong message in response to the #metoo movement and how we can move forward. composing the music for this piece came pretty easily thanks to alayna’s powerful and decisive vision. the best arrangements in my opinion are when it just feels right- you can always lean on that.

text:
#metoo? .
.
i was working on a webpage when the train came whistling to the platform. i stood up sliding forth my trolley, and took a moment to move it to the raised train bogie. just two hours and i'll be home! .
.
'jaldi chadhiye madam. nahi to aapka pani hum pee lenge.’ .
.

it took me a moment to decipher that it didn't have anything to do with the gravity working on my green bottle. i turned back, stern - it wasn't fear, neither courage. he was quick to defend himself citing his thirst until he took a step back. perhaps my turning back was a revelation. i went ahead and sat close to a bunch of middle aged men. that could be my safest choice on an half-empty early morning train. he took a seat right next to them, greeted them with a 'jai shri ram’. they shared a laugh discussing the usual namo-raga. he left soon after and i never reported him.

it wasn't fear. it wasn't courage. neither was it shame or 'log kya kahenge’! it was just a rational voice telling me that the effort would be a futile one. that things wouldn't change. that some perverts would keep intruding with sexually offending remarks and would keep getting away with that. it has happened before. it will keep happening. in the schools. in the safest of homes. in the buses and trains.

i am typing this on the same train. the fields are passing by. it's home in a couple more hours. it isn't the first time on a train. i have faced it before, millions face it daily. oh, and i have been lucky to avoid a scene so far, just like today. .

#metoo #indianrailways #train #trainjourney #travel

text:
@100womeniknow
・・・
"rapist" is such a loaded word, many would hate to associate such a word with their friends and family. statistically, we all know rapists. most rape is perpetrated within the home, with someone the victim knows. we must dispel the myth that rapists are evil predators creeping in the dark. we need to broaden the understanding of what rape is.
-
rape can be life changing, violent and horrific, but it can also be more subtle, like sex as a result of coercion and manipulation.
-
we need to better understand what it is to perpetrate; and why such acts have been normalised.
-
we need to move past the blame of self and other and recognise this as a societal, cultural, global problem that we must all work together to change.
-
we must open the conversations. 
we must believe people when they come forward. 
we must not defend and protect rapists, however much they mean to us. 
we must educate the youth, so that perhaps they won’t become perpetrators or victims.
-
art by @hexelot

-
-
-

@earthlove777
• • • • •
rp @jessyforthevoiceless 
graphic footage - cows can only produce milk after giving birth, so dairy farms have to constantly forcibly impregnate the cows. 
as a result, many baby calves are born. 
since male calves will never produce milk, they are of no use to a dairy farm. ▪ 
some farms let the calves live for a few months in order to slaughter them for veal.
an analysis shows that it can cost a farmer up to £30 per calf to sell it on for beef or veal, while 'early disposal' costs just £9.
▪ 
as seen, the workers shoot days-old calves in the head, then leave them to bleed in a mass grave. 
the worker doesn’t even make any special effort to shoot the calves in a way that will deliver a quick death. 
in addition, each calf only gets one bullet in order to save costs.
(this footage is from a dairy farm in florida).
but make no mistake, this happens all over the world.
----------------------------------------------------------------------
reposted from @lebanesevegans - just a normal and legal practice under the umbrella of “humane” slaughter. you can stop this by not buying dairy anymore. alternatives are everywhere.
.

text:
during this period i wasn't allowed to have friends. 
one by one he would drive them away. phone usage was monitored. anything out of the ordinary was met with questioning, anger & jealousy. 
for awhile i obeyed. 
it was the game i lived.
so so often i was accused of cheating even if i was talking to a girl-friend. 
well i got sick of it and i knew better & if he was accusing me so harshly he must have something he's hiding. •
•
•
--story caution--
i was smart and waited till he was in the shower. i opened the door and grabbed his phone. he must be hiding something i thought.
he jumped out of that shower like his ass was on fire and chased me. i tossed it back. no sense in getting beat. but still i wanted to know so i stepped back into the bathroom and grabbed it. he must have not heard me because he didn't chase me this time. 
i opened the messages. 
i knew i would find something. some evidence, ya know.
i was not ready for what i saw. 
multiple girls. girls we both hung out with & an ex. 
i sat there crying. i loved him.
and then i felt him standing behind me. i didn't move. i was caught. he grabbed my hair & twisted it in his hand and slammed my head against the wall. i'm shocked.
i always thought that this wouldn't happen again.
i was fighting for my life. 
punching + kicking, anything i could do. 
as i'm picturing this fight it's a blur but i do remember him throwing me into the wall and running back over to grab my hair for the last time to beat me into the floor. he let me go. 
grabbed his phone and left for the night.

that night i laid with my cat and thanked god i was still alive. terrified for when he would return.
•
•
•
•
•
•

text:
in full transparency y’all... i do not have it all together. 
and i have days where i struggle. 
today i woke up to our electricity off, freezing cold. 
and found out it is expected back thursday early evening. 
i’ve been frustrated all day. 
i had plans to crush my monday! 
got up at 5, prayed with the team. got the kids to school 
and then rushed out of my house because i couldn’t stand the cold anymore. 
none of the planned things have gotten done. 
and my frustrations of not wanting to deal with this alone truthfully has had me on the verge of tears. 
i’ve been short of cuss words pulling the dang wood up my hill, the fire won’t light... and yes frustration got the most of me

it’s not that i can’t do it, it’s that i truthfully don’t want to .
some days i can super human power through, but today for some reason just wasn’t one of those days. 
when god designed a marriage and said 2 became 1, he meant it! 
the jobs of two people , became one, a house hold. 
divorce splits the 1, into 2, but not the work load. 
you now are 1 person trying to do the work of 2. 
so i’ve got brokenness... i still have work to be done... and i totally suck sometimes, but i am thankful for god’s blessings amongst it as he used my 7 year old to put things in perspective. 
my middle son, snapped me out of my funk real quick when he was watching me frustrated... and says to me “ but mom, at least we have a house to light a fire in! some people don’t even have that.” and he is right. 
it’s a total jerk move of me to even be so frustrated about this. 
so many people have it way worse... and i am thankful for my sweet spirited caleb, to point that out. 
it’s ok to get frustrated and upset and not be ok with certain things, but the key is to put it in perspective... dont stay there. 
thank you my c, for that beautiful reminder. ♥️

i’m going to share a story with you guys that my physics teacher told my class. back in 1989, when she was a chemical engineer major in uni, she was one of the only two girls in her year. is that not insane that 30 years ago women were struggling to major in stem?!? and not because they lacked intelligence but because, of two things. 
1. some girls would purposely dumb themselves down for a guy because it was “cute” even though they weren’t dumb at all. 
2. they weren’t given the same opportunities that their male counterparts got.
it’s just so insane to me that things have changed to that amount. -

text:
not many people know my story, they don’t know that i was abused every day of my youth. whether it was thru physical abuse, the scars that healed, or thru mental and emotional abuse, the scars i’m still dealing with.
*
i tend to not share my story, as much as i should, bc i don’t ever want to sound like i am complaining about my past. *
there are those that aren’t fortunate enough to have escaped their suffering and must live with their abusers.
*
healing from your traumas is a choice. you can choose to remain a victim or you can choose to overcome your past. *
i have chosen the latter.

text:
bom, a moda que me interessa é aquela que funciona como uma crônica da atualidade, que registra o espírito do tempo e até mesmo cria mudanças sociais. baseada nisso, aí vão os meus selecionados como pontos altos do #oscars 2019

1. é muito poder reunido em uma só foto. @madonna e @ladygaga juntas, será que passamos daquela fase que tivemos aqui no brasil de beijinho no ombro, não sei o que pras inimigas. ai, que cansativo. será que a #sororidade reina junto com essas duas rainhas mesmo?
🎭
2. o look de @theebillyporter quebrou a internet, e quebra também a dureza entre o vestir masculino e feminino. well done, @csiriano (your fan since project runway!)
🎭
3. regina king @iamreginaking, toda clássica, com sua fenda e ombros à mostra, inclusive isso é uma tendência em alta, muitos, mas muitos vestidos com esse detalhe.
🎭
4. jason momoa @prideofgypisies, o legal aqui é um homem desse usando rosa, e o detalhe de uma scrunchie (acessório para prender o cabelo que nós chamávamos de ´calcinha`nos 80 e 90) usada no braço suaviza ainda mais o look. ficou lindo, amo o smoking por ser de veludo tbm. o ponto negativo é que se a gente for olhar com atenção as proporções do blazer não estão tão boas, está meio curto pra ele.
🎭
5. halleloo! é a @itsshangela do @rupaulsdragrace, amo! viciada em assistir as drags competirem.
🎭
6. @officialspikelee, só tenho uma coisa a dizer: #dotherightthing
🎭
7. @therealruthecarter, maravilhosa, ganha oscar de melhor figurino por #blacpanther. que pesquisa, que desenvolvimento, que show. esse figurino será sempre lembrado na história do cinema. 🎭
8. @melissamccarthy veste @brandonmaxwell, de calça, toda fina, gostei muito!
🎭
9. a @emilia_clarke eu pus aqui pq gosto dela, mas repare bem que essa cor de cabelo é um pouco escura para ela que é verão suave como eu.já o vestido tem uma cor perfeita para o seu subtom de pele.
🎭
10. e o rosa não sai mais das paradas de sucesso, antes ela era vista como uma cor de barbie, mas hoje foi ressignificada e apropriada para a causa #feminista (#feminismo) e o movimento #metoo.

text:
grateful to have caroline macgillivray part of our panel for this year's international women's day program in vancouver
.
.
caroline macgillivray designs workshops and programs to promote health and wellness in the corporate and not for profit sector. caroline is a popular speaker, writer, medical qi gong therapist, yoga teacher and workshop leader.  she believes we need to unplug, breathe and be. she is has been involved with  initiatives such as qi day and bunny yoga fundraising classes for small animal rescue. she has also taught workshops for kids and parents for safe online outreach society.  caroline is best known for founding beauty night society, an award-winning charity that provides programs to build self esteem and change the lives of vulnerable people through wellness, life skills development and make overs. in 18 years, beauty night society has given 70, 000 life-makeovers to women who live in poverty.
.
. 
the well beings & weekend rituals (march 4, 9 & 10)
https://iwd2019vancouver.eventbrite.ca or the link in @minibarcanada's profile.

text:
we were taught that no is a dirty word and if we use it we will lose opportunities. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
saying no means, while i do love you, but it’s best that i take a break and rest, rather than adding another project to my already full inbox. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
saying no means, while i think you’re cute, but i don’t want to have sex. i will when and if i feel like it and that choice will be mine. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
saying no means, i’m your friend but declining that invite because that event doesn’t align with my values. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
saying no means.... it means no, so please respect it and understand. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
i was supposed to have the weekend “off” for my friend’s bachelorette party, but got the flu instead. sometimes shit just happens. anyway, the few times i did see my friends, my husband made himself very useful and was being very generous and kind to everyone and of course, treating me like a queen in front of them all. well today everyone left and i’m feeling a little better so i decided to have brunch with them before they took off for the airport. he attempted to sabotage that by saying we “needed to talk about today’s plans” and my mother, who was in town to watch the kids, recognized what he was doing so she said, “i just ordered you an uber and it will be here in 4 minutes.” he was pissed. i took off and he proceeded to stand in the driveway looking at me like i was getting into my lover’s car—very angry. and then the texts started...”i deserve a fucking award” (for doing the things he volunteered for) and that my “words are very hurtful” (?). he was just mad that i was having brunch with my friends 🤷🏻‍♀️ anyway, time for the other him to re-emerge. all of the girls are gone so he’s back to being himself, whoever that is. •
•

this week i had the pleasure of hearing from dr. michael kaufman. a public speaker, author and educator, whose work focuses on engaging men and boys to promote gender equality. he’s also the co-founder of the white ribbon campaign – which is the largest network of men working to end violence against women.⁣
⁣
in his new book “the time has come: why men must join the gender equality revolution”, he shares what men stand to gain in the fight for gender equality, and what actions they can take to become better advocates for women.⁣
⁣
listen to the episode at the link in my bio to learn more about his book and the inspiration behind his work. ⬆️🎧.⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣

text: on friday, @mindykaling received pushback from followers after posting on instagram that she’d attended comedian @azizansari's stand-up show. ansari has recently begun performing again after a story published in babe magazine last year — in which a woman said she felt pressured into sex on a date with him — sparked a conversation about consent in the #metoo era. many fans were upset that kaling attended the show and publicly endorsed it. kaling, for her part, responded to some of the comments. “i think it would be cowardly to be his friend and not come to his defense when people disparage him in public,” she wrote. “obviously i don’t love responding to instagram comments late on a friday night but i’m a feminist and standing up for women is very important to me. i’m not rehabbing him bc i think he did a fine job doing it himself.” (photo by reuters; illustration by @thelilynews)

text:
someone asked me what my recent instagram posts were about and whether i wrote and blogs that went into a little more depth. 
and it got me thinking, although i try to be as open with my readers as possible, i realize that i haven’t been as clear about my intentions with this blog as i probably should have.
yes, there is a blog, it’s called words from the heart and it’s on my website, which i’ll link here. 
the blog is an exploration of the rape culture in australia and around the world, the survivor’s story and my own. my aim with this blog has been to educate and to highlight the insecurities many survivors experience after their assault and why so many go unreported. it’s also there to teach us that we don’t know everyone’s story, insensitive comments and jokes can affect people and trigger them in ways most could never understand.
as with all my work, it’s raw and unfiltered, which of course can be unnerving for some, please speak to someone if you’re affected or need help.
and as always, reach out to me, i love hearing your stories and how my work has impacted you, after all, this is why i write; to challenge your beliefs, to challenge the norm and to encourage you to ask questions.
#survivorstories #survivorsunite #calloutthebullshit #metoo #advocateforwomen #nomeansno #findyourvoice #nomoresilence #wearefierce #wearesurvivors #wearestrong #sexualassault #rapecultureisreal #rapeculturemustfall #lifeblogger #survivorblog

text:
here i am at 17. it’s the year 2000 and i had just moved across the country from miami to la after saving money i made from modeling, acting and working at the gap (hence my adversity to folding clothing). i didn’t know a soul, but i was stubborn as all hell and knew i needed to follow my dreams of being an actor. i knew the only way i would ever “make it” would be by leaving home.
....
with ‘felicity’ on my mind and dido’s 'no angel' album playing on repeat though my walkman, i felt empowered. dare i say, even independent. i didn’t have a car and the rollerblades i brought along as my form of transit quickly began to collect dust as i learned the true meaning of “public transportation”. it was just me and my thomas guide map tucked in the pocket of my jansport backpack exploring the crazy world of hollywood, one bus ride after another.
....
by 17, i had already been sexually assaulted by 6 different men. all much older, some even well known. let me repeat that, by 17, i had already been sexually assaulted by six men. if i only knew what i know now, i would save myself. i would save myself from all the anguish caused by guilt and shame, as if i had deserved to be treated like an object.
....
i wish i could say it ended here, but it didn’t. i went on to experience even more assault. at 19, i almost went to court against a man, an employer i worked for, who had raped me. i was terrified of what people would think and that fear prevented me from taking further action. i allowed his team of lawyers to scare me back into the shadows while i quietly signed an nda, all the while still thinking “i deserved it”.
....
i quickly became a lost soul who could not fill her void, no matter how hard she tried. i ran away from one feeling after the next, but eventually, it all caught up with me. a few of the men who have harmed me are in jail now or have been wanted by the fbi or have put a gun to their very own head rather than face trial…some you watch on your television daily. i share this publicly for one reason and one reason only. to let this 17 year old girl and all the rest of you out there know you are not alone. #metoo
....
cont⬇️...

text: i felt so sickened after watching surviving r kelly last month. i’m so happy he’s in jail and can’t pay bail. there’s nothing worse than a molester, abuser, manipulator, and brainwasher of children. i can’t imagine how hard it is to overcome the trauma that the women in the series have had. i found an article by @leafly connecting sexual assault and cannabis usage aiding in relief and promoting the long-term healing process after trauma. 📖 the article states that research on human subjects have shown that the compounds in cannabis, both thc and cbd, can enhance our capacity for fear extinction, a scientific term for what happens in the brain when therapy (or just everyday life in a safe and loving environment) helps a trauma survivor change their response to stimuli that would have previously triggered symptoms like anxiety, panic, and flashbacks. the cannabinoids literally promote the kind of brain changes needed to release limiting patterns of thought and behavior. 🌱 cannabis is such a promising plant for alternative treatments in so many problem areas. thankfully the cannabis community has created such an impact as a whole and finally were seeing policy changes not based on just getting high 💨

text: last year's "film for change" award went to "lady m" a film that highlighted the need for more diverse roles for women on screen. the film also shined light on the disparity of gender equality in the film industry. tammy riley-smith (the director) and karen newman (the producer) were supported by a largely female led cast and crew in a film that has gone on to win multiple awards and numerous festival selections. bolton film festival embraces the values of the f-rating and bechdel test, we look to the future for an equal and level playing field for all in society. we're open for entries now at filmfreeway. #womeninfilm #reclaimtheframe #metoo #calltoaction #filmfestival #filmmaker #indiefilm #drama #documentary #animation  #comedy #studentfilm #manchester #bolton #events #competition #filmfreeway

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

warning: sexual assault/harassment/rape 
he was my volleyball coach and we had gotten really close. one night i didn’t have a ride to one of the games and he offered to give me a ride. i said yes because it was nothing out of the ordinary, he had given me ride before. then when we arrived at the school, he parked really far away from the other cars. something didn’t feel right. i tried to get out but he said he wanted to talk to me first, he the proceeded to gently touch my legs and kiss me. he got on top of me and i tried to say no but he just said “i know you want this. i can tell.” he took my hands off and held me down and raped me. after, we went into the game like nothing even happened. #metoo #metoomovement #metoomvmt #nomore

text:
@ourindianculture.us team would like to congratulate @ritasehmi1 as one of the award winners of "women achievers awards," to be given at pretty in pink-women empowerment gala, celebrating women's day (tickets link in bio) 
as the owner of @dreamraytalent
rita sehmi, has been in the forefront of the entertainment industry for the past eighteen years. holding an mba in advertising marketing, she has had first-hand experience as an advertising executive, talent agent, actress, model, and most importantly as a mother. her experience has included work behind the scenes and in front of the camera for film, television, radio, theater, commercial and print.

she started dreamray model and talent two and a half years ago in hopes of giving children of all ethnicities and backgrounds the opportunity to pursue their passion of acting and modeling. growing up as a child wanting to be an actress herself, her mom had no idea of where to go. when she did find avenues of potential opportunities most those places turned out to be scams. rita promised herself that one day she would give as many children as she could the opportunities she did not get a chance to have.

since opening, the agency has become the fastest growing children's talent agency in southern california. with over 300 children being represented by dreamray, many of the kids have been booked for commercials and print ads for companies like disney, walmart, ford, instagram, target, old navy, to name a few.

text:
when i look back on how i created this video campaign i cannot believe it! in those days i wasn't a cumputer wizards (nothing has really changed since then) 😅 i used flash and each letter was moved one by one /frame by frame. this was complete dedication and trust that the end result would be as powerful as possible. i would be interested in hearing your thoughts on it. .
. 
each act of violence can work as a catalyst for what may become profound experiences of shock and torment. in this video, the cotton thread, the increase in pace of the needle, the disturbing and hammering sound becoming increasingly louder, are symbolic of this gradual movement towards emotional turmoil.
.
.

text:
the dragonfly’s tale
the bear swatted at the dragonfly
simply because she had darted into his field of vision.
he was too big and full of himself to bother
with being polite to such a tiny creature.
she though small
was fast,
and very,
very,
smart.
she darted out of the way of 
his massive paw again and again
but he finally managed to catch the tip of her wing
and tear it with his claw,
crippling her flight.
she escaped by clinging to one of the sycamore seeds,
shaken down from the tree by the bumbling bear.
camouflaging herself,
she spun away in the breeze
leaving him to flail
in circles,
as he splashed into the river,
trying to find her.
confused by all the seeds 
twirling like helicopters,
he did not notice the waterfall until
too late and plunging over,
he was gone.
a golden fish swam into view
who saw it all and lifting her fins
she tossed a scale to the dragonfly,
who thanked her
and used it to patch her wing. 
the fish, no lover of bears either,
whispered the tale
to amuse a frog
who told it to a dear
at the water’s edge
and that is how word spread
that bears are no match 
for the cunningness
of the dragonfly. #dragonfly #dragonflies #feministpoetry #womenspoetry #poetry #instapoetry #survivor #metoo
name: Cathleen Thole Daniels

text: #motivationmonday wekelijks onthullen wij welke bijzondere gasten onderdeel uitmaken van het inspire to move women up: black girl magic edition programma. met trots kondigen wij aan dat neerlandicus, journalist, @tedx-spreker en fashion-cultuuractivist, @janice.deul te gast is als onze keynote spreker! 🔥🙌🔥🙌 afkomstig uit de bladenwereld, waar @janice.deul als eindredacteur werkte voor tal van lifestyle titels, maakt zij zich al jaren sterk voor meer diversiteit in mode👘👒, media en – meer recentelijk – de culturele sector en de creatieve industrie. ze is co-auteur van little black hair book, een boek met haarverhalen en -geheimen van afro-dutch vrouwen en is - met name sinds haar deelname aan de talkshow @pauwnl een belangrijke stem in het debat. ook is ze met enige regelmaat te zien in de @omroepntr-talkshow @denieuwemaan en het rtl 4-ochtendmagazine @koffietijd.5uurlive waar ze net zo makkelijk spreekt over #metoo, black hair en de arabische modeweek als over politieke correctheid en het heersende schoonheidsideaal💅💇‍♀️. thema’s die ze veelvuldig aan de orde stelt middels talks, workshops, opiniestukken, gastcolleges, door haarzelf gecureerde events en op haar inspiratieplatform @diversity_rules. en sinds kort schittert zij op de cover van het blad @opzijmagazine.😍 op 8 maart komt @janice.deul de bezoekers van inspire to move women up: black girl magic edition empoweren in @tsh_thehague. wil jij dit niet missen? bestel hier👆🏾je ticket

let's not believe the stereotypes that  men are all guns, violence and football. men have emotions too, and at the core of feminism is the fight against the patriarchy and the certain types of masculinity that is so toxic it has hurt both men, women, and the like. we are feminists, you, me, him, her, them, and our battle is against the social constructs that tell women they are weak by nature, and men they are weak if they have emotions. rejoice, and push onward.

.
.
.
.
.

text: jag vaknade och det var blod på väggen, i lakanen och på golvet och jag hade en plastpåse över huvudet. det är 12 månader sedan jag överlevde mitt självmord. det är också 12 månader sedan jag startade det här kontot. jag tänkte skriva något på ”årsdagen”, men jag hittade inte orden. jag hittar fortfarande inte riktigt orden. för ett år sedan var jag less. jag var less på att sälja mig själv, jag var less på droger, jag var less på alla runtomkring mig, jag var less på mitt liv. men framförallt var jag less på torskarna. samma dag som jag vaknade från mitt självmordsförsök började jag posta skärmdumpar från konversationer med torskar. jag taggade alla möjliga konton som jag hoppades skulle se eller höra vad jag ville dela. jag tror att väldigt få vet att jag postade inläggen för att avstyra ännu ett självmordsförsök, och att jag behövde aktivismen för att skaka av mig alla tankar om att mitt liv var över. jag har sänt live från torskars lägenheter, jag har sänt live både full och hög. jag har skrivit fyllerim i stories och postat bilder på när torskar knullat mig. det kanske inte alltid känts bra dagen efter, för mig.. jag har skrivit om prostitution i över ett års tid. jag har hittat gemenskapen i @intedinhora och varit en del av #metoo. jag har gått från att sitta och knarka, sälja sex och vilja dö till att bli drogfri, lycklig och studera sen jag startade mitt konto. för ett år sedan låg jag och skakade av heroinabstinens i den här sängen, vägde alldeles för lite, hade färska sår på hela kroppen och var omringad av tomma flaskor med butangas. för ett år sedan träffade jag torskar flera gånger om dagen och trodde aldrig jag skulle bli fri. idag ligger jag i samma säng. normalviktig, utan minsta drogsug, känner mig hoppfull, lycklig, fri och vill inget hellre än att leva för evigt. om jag bara visste för några år sedan hur allting skulle bli. tänk om jag visste då att allt tillslut skulle ordna sig. jag minns inte senast jag tog en drog eller träffade en torsk. men jag vet att jag uppskattat varje dag sen jag överlevde mitt självmordsförsök. vilket år 😱❤️#metoo #prostitution #intedinhora #missbruk

text: #motivationmonday wekelijks onthullen wij welke bijzondere gasten onderdeel uitmaken van het inspire to move women up: black girl magic edition programma. met trots kondigen wij aan dat neerlandicus, journalist, @tedx-spreker en fashion-cultuuractivist, @janice.deul te gast is als onze keynote spreker! 🔥🙌🔥🙌 afkomstig uit de bladenwereld, waar @janice.deul als eindredacteur werkte voor tal van lifestyle titels, maakt zij zich al jaren sterk voor meer diversiteit in mode👘👒, media en – meer recentelijk – de culturele sector en de creatieve industrie. ze is co-auteur van little black hair book, een boek met haarverhalen en -geheimen van afro-dutch vrouwen en is - met name sinds haar deelname aan de talkshow @pauwnl een belangrijke stem in het debat. ook is ze met enige regelmaat te zien in de @omroepntr-talkshow @denieuwemaan en het rtl 4-ochtendmagazine @koffietijd.5uurlive waar ze net zo makkelijk spreekt over #metoo, black hair en de arabische modeweek als over politieke correctheid en het heersende schoonheidsideaal💅💇‍♀️. thema’s die ze veelvuldig aan de orde stelt middels talks, workshops, opiniestukken, gastcolleges, door haarzelf gecureerde events en op haar inspiratieplatform @diversity_rules. en sinds kort schittert zij op de cover van het blad @opzijmagazine.😍 op 8 maart komt @janice.deul de bezoekers van inspire to move women up: black girl magic edition empoweren in @tsh_thehague. wil jij dit niet missen? bestel hier👆🏾je tickets: http://urbanchickswithbrains.com/itmwu-tickets/

text:
the danish maritime association, lederne søfart, is kickstarting a research regarding sexual harashments at sea. it is an important topic that we in co-operation with niras want to put on the agenda. 
we need to be able to speak about these kind of things. we are all just humanbeings - men or women - and if you have been object to any kind of harashment it should be okay to speak up about it, witbout you feeling wrong. i hope the maritime industry will support the project in any way possible and i hope my colleagues out there will be strong enough to tell the truth.

“hi there! my name is becca—you can call me bex if you want.
.
i’m a passionate yoga teacher, retreat leader, blogger, author, international holistic health coach and dream-life coach. before this, i went from suicidal, self-hatred and self-harm to thriving, self-love, and self-respect.
.
gratefully now i’m in love with my body, my life, my journey and how perfectly imperfect it all is. with the help of many simple yet powerful tools, support and inspiration, as well as taking scary leaps, i was able to heal myself from my depression and create something magical.”
.

text:
did i know you in my past life? 
i feel like we’ve met before
who knew that you were here all along
time passing by, waiting for us to meet again
when we met, we became one 
back in each other’s arms feeling like i could finally breathe again 
you made everything easier , life with you felt right
they say everything happens for a reason 
but i can’t help but think what’s the reason for this? for us? 
i guess it’s all gods plan..
someone watching over us, guiding us through this journey called life
we’re all just walking around trying to make sense of the world
but when i found you, i knew that i had all i needed 
when i look at you, i see opportunities to know love , true love #godsplan #frankocean

text:
love at first sight
i didn’t know it would happen that night 
the look in your eyes,
i wanted to stare forever 
you made me feel lighter than a feather
the way u kissed my lips and put your hands in my hair,
i couldn’t help but fall deeper in love
and i didn’t even care
i forget all my problems when with you
this feeling i got is brand new
now you have my heart
and the key to my soul
when you came into my life, 
i finally began to feel whole
thank you for loving all my flaws, 
without you, life would have no cause 
you are my light and my heart 
i pray to god that we will never be apart

text:
poetry
these words, these phrases
they heal me, they talk to me, 
they put me in a daze
typing out the thoughts in my mind
it comes out like word vomit
throwing up the mess thats inside
its like writing is the only thing that has my back
if i can reach anybody, even one person
then my purpose has been fulfilled
it takes one person, one mind, one soul
to change another
the world creates this domino effect all on its own
i want everyone to know,
i too, cry and feel
you are not alone
my heart has been broken in ways you don’t know, 
i’m sure you can relate
rather than dwell on the past, 
pick up the phone and call an old friend
ask them to meet you somewhere 
don’t listen to that voice in your head 
saying “no, lets stay in bed”.
accept what you are feeling 
but, don’t let it consume you
tell others your thoughts on depression
do not be scared of their expression
speak about your deepest confessions
keeping it all in, will only lead to regression #poetry #writing #helpingothers

text:
you take up my entire brain capacity
they say we only use 10% of our brains
but the other 90% is going to you..
the hurt you caused me, 
its playing on repeat in my head
make it stop- that’s all i want
i wish i could close my eyes
and erase you from my memory 
thinking back to who i was before you
wow, i can’t even remember that girl
i miss her, i want her back
what’s her name again?#poetry #blogger #positivity

text:
you tell me i’m the closest thing to perfect that you know, 
meanwhile i can’t help but think of myself so low
you’ve done more for me than even, you know 
i feel a lot more for you than what i show..
your presence would be the hardest thing to ever let go
alone in this world, but i feel complete with you 
i wanna tell the truth to you 
i wanna talk about my time as a youth to you 
exposing you to all my demons and the reasons i’m this way 
i wish i could tell you everything but, it’ll take more than a day 
it will take more than some years to get over all of my fears 
the wall i spent so much time building 
is finally crashing down, creating an ocean of my tears 
even tho i’m too scared to expose myself, 
it turns out, you know me better than i know myself 
thank you for always coming to the rescue 
you’re like my guardian angel, i thank god for you #shesminept1 #poetry

text:
✨new work✨where all my peeps with anxiety at?! 🙋🏻‍♀️💯. i personally don’t speak specifically about my mental health to insta.  i do to a select few people and might open up lil bit more here.  however, i’ve tricked you into thinking all my love note paintings were only for others.  muahaha.  i could call them all self portraits... anyways i digress. 🌪

anxiety: what a an annoying thing.  i think i’ve always had a bit of low rumbling anxiety, but due to some life events it’s really heightened.  i’ve been thinking of ways i could visually represent the feeling of anxiety.  this is just one way i’ve chosen. 
a simple gold line representing life/soul/being and around it is the chaotic energy of anxiety.  you are still there even, when you don’t feel there cuz this thing, this weight has you surrounded.  soon breaths are short, vision is impaired and the heart is racing. 🌪

but then you remember you are still there, one deep slow breath, inhale, exhale, inhale, exhale.  you find your center again.  you didn’t go anywhere, it’s just as if you were attacked, pillaged, ransacked. 
i hope for this painting and others will represent that idea in the most simplistic form.  it might change a little since this is just the beginning. 🌪

#mentalhealth #anxiety #painting #artheals #artaethetics #bethedifference
#oktosay #hereforyou #lookforthehelpers #metoo #bethedifference #wagepeace #orangetheworld #wordsthatmatter  #believesurvivors #seizetheawkward #artaesthetics #becomegoodnews

but then you remember you are still there, one deep slow breath, inhale, exhale, inhale, exhale.  you find your center again.  you didn’t go anywhere, it’s just as if you were attacked, pillaged, ransacked. 
i hope for this painting and others will represent that idea in the most simplistic form.  it might change a little since this is just the beginning. 🌪

     ethedifference

this was created the morning after the @oprah speech at the oscars last year.  this morning i woke up to a post that @taranajaneen activist, badass, and creator of the #metoo movement would be speaking at notre dame this evening. as a contemporary artist, activist, and social worker i had a joy overcome me. the art i do reflects the importance of being seen. my life has lead up to being seen. i have witnessed so many of these moments that turn into a movement. a movement larger than one individual, a movement to be seen. tell your story. live in your own light. cant wait to hear you speak @taranajaneen👑👑 #crownon .
.

text:
“hi there! my name is becca—you can call me bex if you want

i’m a passionate yoga teacher, retreat leader, blogger, author, speaker, international holistic health coach and dream-life coach. 
i went from suicidal, self-hatred and self-harm to thriving, self-love, and self-respect.

gratefully now i’m in love with my body, my life, my journey and how perfectly imperfect it all is. with the help of many simple yet powerful tools, support and inspiration, as well as taking scary leaps, i was able to heal myself from my depression and create something magical.” becca from @beccathornewellness is a rockstar and a survivor of sexual trauma. read her story: https://iamarockstar.me/portfolio-items/becca/

share your rockstar story, join our healing groups and find resources at our website. 
link in bio.

text:
my older sister amie’s got a photographic memory, she says to me, i can see it like a movie, him beating you. 
i was just 2, small, fragile, and helpless, but my sister was selfless, and tried her damndest to try and protect me from my own daddy. 
i don’t remember, what a blessing, keeps me from stressing, until i heard what he did to her. 
our daddy was a sicko and you should know, that my mother was weak and wouldn’t leave him, for good that is, always goin back like a dog to a bone, because she was scared and didnt wanna be alone. 
two sick parents, 2 traumatized daughters makes for such a fucking happy family, hiding behind christianity and making everything look pretty when in truth it’s ugly and shitty. 
abusive boyfriends, eating disorders, drugs and rebellion, sexual promiscuity, abortion and rape, how much more could i possibly take? 
but we grew up, through all the ugly and made it pretty, even through all that shitty. we met our husbands and had our own babies, it wasn’t all roses and daisies but we stopped the cycle of abuse and made it out ok. 
and now we’re older, a lot wiser, friends with our sons, daughters and we’re fighters. a true story from me to you, to whom this may concern, me too.

text:
am i , knock, knock, knockin on heavens door, like guns n roses said, is that cold black cloud comin down, to go with the dreaded frown, placed on my face by my cousin who’s a sicko, and a disgrace to the human race. 
made me feel ashamed, embarrassed, dirty, why the hell did i let him touch me? beats me, maybe because i was 8 , he told me it was ok, and i laid in wait for the abuse that i would take. 
i told my mamma, my sister, who told my aunt his mamma, my mamas sister,  who was a loving bitch who said she’s lying, just like his step daughter whom he’s in jail for abusing now instead of frying. 
karmas a bitch just like my aunt who didn’t believe me or his step daughter, or did she? i know the truth just like she did, and tried to lie and nobody believed her. just like me i wonder if it hurts her, it must because it’s just. 
her sons incarcerated, being abused and taking it up the ass just like they love to do to a child molester or monster, sorry to sound gross or crass, but this is truth and even through my trauma and all the drama i’m not sorry for feeling justified through all the tears i’ve cried. 
because even through all the sickness, dysfunction, i got up the gumption to grow up, move on, be more, see that i wasn’t a whore. 
that i was special, and i deserved some form of heaven,  because as god is my witness he knows i’ve already experienced hell in some form, just remember it’s not the norm, it’s your body, you own it, your in control, and thank god they will never listen to my cousins bull shit and let him out on parole. 
and now this letters ending, and i’m sharing my tears and sorrow, and where ever you are in your pain it’s not in vein, you are loved and you are more, and you are not a whore. and once again i will be at peace knowing that i’m not alone, that i have grown into a fighter with a voice that’s loud and true, and once again to whom this may concern, me too.

tweet_full:
am i , knock, knock, knockin on heavens door, like guns n roses said, is that cold black cloud comin down, to go with the dreaded frown, placed on my face by my cousin who’s a sicko, and a disgrace to the human race. 
made me feel ashamed, embarrassed, dirty, why the hell did i let him touch me? beats me, maybe because i was 8 , he told me it was ok, and i laid in wait for the abuse that i would take. 
i told my mamma, my sister, who told my aunt his mamma, my mamas sister,  who was a loving bitch who said she’s lying, just like his step daughter whom he’s in jail for abusing now instead of frying. 
karmas a bitch just like my aunt who didn’t believe me or his step daughter, or did she? i know the truth just like she did, and tried to lie and nobody believed her. just like me i wonder if it hurts her, it must because it’s just. 
her sons incarcerated, being abused and taking it up the ass just like they love to do to a child molester or monster, sorry to sound gross or crass, but this is truth and even through my trauma and all the drama i’m not sorry for feeling justified through all the tears i’ve cried. 
because even through all the sickness, dysfunction, i got up the gumption to grow up, move on, be more, see that i wasn’t a whore. 
that i was special, and i deserved some form of heaven,  because as god is my witness he knows i’ve already experienced hell in some form, just remember it’s not the norm, it’s your body, you own it, your in control, and thank god they will never listen to my cousins bull shit and let him out on parole. 
and now this letters ending, and i’m sharing my tears and sorrow, and where ever you are in your pain it’s not in vein, you are loved and you are more, and you are not a whore. and once again i will be at peace knowing that i’m not alone, that i have grown into a fighter with a voice that’s loud and true, and once again to whom this may concern, me too.

text:
i once loved a boy madly, completely, obsessively, because i needed love that desperately. didn’t get it from my daddy, i know, same sad story you’ve heard it all before, but this is my tale so let me tell you how i grew up, moved on, and shut that door and became so much more. 
we were both hurting in different ways, from different parents, on different days, we loved, we fought, we hurt each other because when that’s what your being taught and your desperate,  you learn that dysfunction isn’t pleasant. it’s ugly and mean and it makes you want to scream at the world, at each other, if only we had different fathers and mothers. 
we had quite a ride, the crazy kids we were, 4 years we tried to make it last, but drugs and life and moving too fast,  we were ruined before we really began and that my friends is how we ran. away from the pain, the dysfunction and shame. 
getting in trouble and doing the worst,  i swear at my young age i thought i was cursed, but he got in trouble much deeper then i, and he went away and i started to cry. it was a cleansing for me for i knew it was the end, but i remembered the times he was my best friend. 
i was lonely once again, or wasn’t i always? and just didn’t know how easy pickings i was for all the wolves at the door, telling me your just a whore, come with me i’ll give you more. 
i learned real quick thanks to my sis, that i was more, that i had a voice, that i wasn’t my pain, my trauma, or my mamma. 
i lived clean, in a loving home with my sister, her husband and my beautiful new born niece who taught me how to love right, big, honestly and healthy and my eyes were opened and my heart was full and i was done being everyone’s fool. i was strong, pretty, smart, and had a lot to give so when i met my husband i was ready to live. 
and now we have beautiful, smart, successful, children whom we’re so proud of, they are the light of my life, and my reward for all i have had to endure. and my husband adores me, and loves me right and that is a love story done right. good night 🙏🏻🌞

text: a little about me and my poetry 💔🙏🏻🌞🔥😏 telling my story of trauma and abuse through poetry, is quite new to me, but it’s helping tremendously with my ptsd, so please just listen and bare with me. i’m not all dreary, i can actually be quite funny, and sexy, so i hope you enjoy all my stories of how i’m healing, dealing, it might send you reeling, but don’t worry about me, i’m healthy and happy, and it’s freeing, me leaving you all my thoughts and feelings, and even some of my sexuality because it’s ok to be, sexual that is, after events that are traumatic, it could be problematic in your relationship or marriage, what ever your dynamic, it can still be fantastic. so start at the beginning when reading my stories, so you can understand where my minds been, where it’s at now, and share in my recovery. because there’s lots of us, and we must share and trust, and be knowing and ok, and live to write and share another day. so if god or the universe has led you to me, i hope you understand and maybe even enjoy some of my story.

text:
“a little bit about me: i’m 29 years old and i work at a nonprofit food relief organization full time as a volunteer and development coordinator. i have a master’s degree in applied anthropology and have traveled to 25 different countries in my lifetime. i love travel more than anything. i would quit my job tomorrow, if i could make a living off of traveling and writing. writing is my 2nd passion next to travel. i especially love writing about travel and have published a book and write a blog. in my book, sisters, sunsets, and self discovery, i found the courage to talk about and tell the world about the sexual assault that i experienced.” - melissa 
melissa from @melissathewanderer is a survivor of sexual assault. read her story: https://iamarockstar.me/portfolio-items/melissa-gittelman/

text:
i never wanted to be the face of #thisisjane, but the universe, as she often does, had other plans. ⠀
so this is me— just moments before the idea to document a community of womxn healing #ptsd with the help of plant medicine was born. somehow i found myself detailing a history of childhood sexual abuse with a photographer i’d just met that morning— tears welling with each word i spoke.⠀
⠀
you see i’d stopped crying actual tears years ago, but in that moment something switched. it was as if something inside of me broke and i felt the twinges of freedom for the first time.
⠀
it was just then, from behind a her lens, the photographer said, “you know— there’s something really powerful happening here.”⠀
⠀
she was right. there is something immensely powerful about finding the courage to say words that used to choke me in the past. that’s what #cannabis has done, though. it introduced me to me & i’m finally not afraid to tell my story. ⠀
⠀
i’m an incest survivor who went on to traumatize myself for years afterwards. i realize now that i didn’t know any better. i didn’t know that it was okay to fall apart; so i did so quietly for decades. by way of drugs, unhealthy relationships, toxic belief systems about myself and my place in the world, crippling fear & insecurity, trauma was the lens through which i saw everything. until cannabis, it was the best i could do. ⠀
⠀
this plant has given me the courage to face all of that; to face the stories i’ve been telling myself for decades, the ones where i’m always the villain and never the victor, and mostly, the ones that have gone on for far too long.⠀
⠀

text:
someone had their first ~beach~day~ over the weekend! 😆 so many pics to choose from, so expect beach pics for the rest of this week! 🤗 i wanted to get a really cute video of her first steps on sand...buuut, she. just. kept. eating it! 🤦🏻‍♀️🙄😑
—
we go to the beach every month! it’s been our family tradition since our son was born (he’ll be 12). it’s so therapeutic and just good for the soul. when i’m there, ailments + disorders go out the window...especially my ocd/germaphobia! i wish every day could be beach day. ☺️
—
p.s. yes, that’s a hairclip in her hair. 😐 can’t wait to be able to take her to the groomer’s!
—

text:
via @fox31denver: denver – state lawmakers are considering what’s known as a "red flag" bill, which would allow the seizure of weapons from persons deemed by a court to pose a significant risk to themselves or to others.

red flag legislation is often associated with mental health issues and mass shootings. colorado’s attorney general believes it could also be lifesaving for victims of domestic violence. “close to 60 percent of the deaths [in domestic violence incidents] come with a firearm,” attorney general phil weiser said. “if you are going to engage in violence, the most likely way that violence turns deadly is a firearm.” weiser says when a spouse seeks a restraining order or protective order in court from their partner, the judge should have the ability to require all firearms be surrendered. “that is something that is very important to address domestic violence, because if we have warning signs but we don’t take protective action, results can be tragic,” he said.

opponents have argued the proposal goes against second amendment rights and may discourage people from seeking help because of a fear of losing their firearms.

however, weiser argues saving lives should be the top priority for colorado. “if someone says, 'i’m so angry, i’m going to use my weapons,' that’s not an idle threat. that’s a red flag,” he said.

the bill will head to the house appropriations committee next, where it is expected to pass.
name: G.R.O.W. Foundation, Inc.

when deciding whether or not to report a sexual assault to the police, it is important to know what will be involved in the process so you can make the decision that is best for you.  remember, the role of the police is to be impartial investigators. when a sexual assault has been reported to the police, officers are responsible for gathering, evaluating, and processing information and/or evidence. they must critically evaluate whether the evidence supports prosecuting the case regardless of their personal feelings.

when you report an assault to the police, you have the option to seek confidential help or  ask the police to conduct an investigation. 
_____________

~
👉 secure reports of rape crimes, abuse and sexual harassment in tertiary institutions. ~
👉 a repository of critical information on specialist health centers, rape-counsellors and legal abuse in the local area. ~
👉 urgent access to medical/counselling/legal aid

text:
the #faxx are in: women create inclusive work places— including in film. why is this important? because time’s up now further reports that, “women directors also hire other women in key behind-the-camera roles.” the hollywood legal org. has also kicked off the #4percentchallenge—to increase the number of women directing major studio films—because only 4% of the top 100 studio films over the last decade have been directed by women. the challenge calls for industry pros “to commit to hiring one female director in the next 18 months.” regina king was the first to take the pledge during her golden globe best supporting actress acceptance speech. and universal filmed entertainment group, led by donna langley, “became the first major studio to except the challenge in january.” (thr) we’re also applauding last nights female winners especially regina king (again!) and back to back first-ever wins by african-american women—black panther’s production designer hannah beachler and costume designer ruth carter! congrats! .
.
.
.

it’s tricky and i struggle with this daily so don’t beat yourself up about it- knowledge is great - it allows for growth.

are you done with people telling you what you can’t do?

i saw the commercial for the movie, “captain marvel”. in the commercial, scenarios are shown of carol danvers getting knocked down - but she keeps getting back up.  the commercial ends with her saying, “i’m kinda done with you telling me what i can’t do”. when i saw that, i yelled “yes!!” how true is it?  many people love to tell us what we cannot do.  let’s be done with them and that messaging.  it’s time we show them what we can do! 💜

georgia skuza (class of 2019): i was born in queens, new york. my parents got a divorce when i was 7 and between 2010 and 2015 i moved three times. i moved to bethlehem a month before starting my freshman year and after years of not knowing where i belonged, i had found it. i have had my ups and downs, as have everyone else, but sometimes you have to go through those hardships to find out who you truly are. 
when i was 12 years old, i was sexually abused. though it is not who i am, like every survivor, the healing process comes with an immense amount of pain. a year ago, i was at the lowest point in my life, and now, i am at my highest. i've used the pain and anger that i had and turned it into something good. in the wake of the parkland, florida school shootings, i organized the walk-out (raising awareness about gun violence and school safety) here at liberty. 
last november, after months of continued healing and in response to the #metoo movement, i decided to organize the women's march on the lehigh valley. i didn't want what happened to me to be my label, so i used my pain and turned it into something good. 
my favorite thing about liberty is the atmosphere and the people in it. i joined the field hockey team as a freshman, and my senior year i was elected as one of the captains. i grew to love the sport and my team. it helped me tremendously through school and life, and i made amazing friends playing it.  in the fall i will be attending thomas jefferson university, to earn a bachelor's of science in law & society. (📸 credit - jasmine chen - lhs photography club) #builtbybethlehem #empower #basdproud #womensmarch #survivor #change #awareness #metoomovement

text:
happy monday ✨ i’ve been quiet for a while about something that many of you know i feel very strongly about. human rights and specifically the #metoomovement . i’ve been healing from my own experience with sexual assault and almost two years have passed...my court date is less than 2 weeks away and it suddenly feels like a tsunami is boiling waiting to wash over my life again. the journey of fighting this case has been slow and frustrating. experiencing what survivors go through to fight a case has shown me why so many people do not want to come forward. it’s a long, tiering, and traumatic process. it feels like every time you almost close that door you have to reopen it again for the justice system. 
anyways what i’m getting at here is that even though i have been quiet about it on socials i still remind those i encounter about how important it is to not stay indifferent to issues that truly matter in this world. 
it’s hard to raise your voice sometimes i get that...there are so many issues coming to light that we tend to question if we have permission to speak, but always keep educating yourself and always ask questions. it’s important to speak your truth. it’s important to stand up for what you believe in.

her campaign began to promote empowerment through empathy among women of color who had experienced sexual abuse. ⁣
⁣
today we celebrate and honor tarana burke. ⁣
⁣

text:
guys won’t understand. what started as a quirky tourist stop, the cardrona bra fence now projects a strong, united chorus of liberated women:
- you can not confine us; we are free
- you can not hide us; we will be seen
- you can not define us; we are each unique
- you can not objectify us; we are more than our sexuality
shout out to the fierce and fiery woman who let her red bra fly high! you, my dear, are my hero. 🙌 #overtheshoulderboulderholder

text: sammy not the smartest cupcake in the shed but definitely the sweetest! #actor #landoan plays that goofball of a friend, which is perfect because that’s exactly who lan is in real life! lan is one of those rare california born folks working and living in beautiful los angeles. as a human with the “youngest child syndrome” we see his passion for the arts really blossom in both his performance and storytelling.  with many years of comedic improv training and stage work, he really blossoms when it comes to escalating humorous situations both in the script and in our everyday lives. there have been quite a few commercials, short films, and miscellaneous gigs for his career and the one realization he has had: his face is perfect for slow-motion. please enjoy lan’s performance as sammy and if you happen to get a chance and want to see what type of photography he does too, check out his work @ggrassphoto. thanks and enjoy #kundalini!

text:
🌎 males, forever the beneficiaries of systems and structures they built to sustain their power, are at the heart of self-inflicted crises in every part of the world.⁣
⁣
the big picture: power corrupts, and societal structures have so far granted men the most power. there are, of course, unscrupulous female leaders. but because there are far fewer of them, the reckoning for men is taking place on a far vaster scale.⁣
⁣
be smart: abuse of power is nothing new. now in the second year of #metoo, women are feeling more empowered to call men out for abuse and discrimination.⁣
⁣
#men #women #power #metoo⁣
🎨: @lazarogamio

text:
@snaf.se och den feministiska föreningen @femmetopiakg slår ihop. gemensamt har vi beslutat att manifestera för våra rättigheter till ett liv utan sexuellt våld av killar. ————————————————————————
#metoo har öppnat upp många personer ögon för det strukturella maktmissbruket som används när sexuella övergrepp begås på oss tjejer. trots detta så ser vi inte den förändring vi vill ha. övergrepp begås, tjejers kroppar skadas och våra medsyskon känner sig varken säkra i den privata eller offentliga sfären. vi kräver bättre sexualundervisning om samtycke, porrkritiska samtal och nolltolerans av sexuella trakasserier från elever och lärare i våra skolkorridorer!
————————————————————————
joina denna fredliga manifestation med oss nu på internationella kvinnodagen den 8e mars klockan 15.00. stöd kampen mot ett samhället där skolan lär dig dina grundläggande rättigheter du har som människa. ingen äger dig, ingen har rätt att skada dig, ett brott ska ses som ett brott inte sopas under mattan. ————————————————————————
vi samlas klockan 15.00 på mynttorget i gamla stan vid riksdagshuset.

text:
wow! today betsy from the us joined for a feminist discovery of santiago and it was an absolute pleasure to hear all about her work and mission.
.
betsy is a criminologist who was deeply involved in the fight against sexual harassment in the 1980s. she's published several books on sexual violence and gender inequality. 
during her trip to chile, betsy has not only visited her friend ximena bunster-burotto but she's determined to get ximena's name and work known. ximena is a chilean activist and feminist who's received several awards and recognition for her contribution to human rights. ximena went into exile after the coup in 73 but came back to continue her work. 
as tours with meaning we will join betsy's mission. now, you'll be able to read ximena's research on mapuche women in our feminist pack to continue learning and we will share her story on our tour.
join us on this feminist tour and find out all about ximena and betsy's incredible work!
.
#inspiringwomen #mujeresinspiradoras #chile #chiletravel #travelchile #travelideas #feminism #niunamenos #metoo #vivasnosqueremos

text_retweet:
|| en este #díanaranja me sumo al rechazo de actos atroces en contra de las mujeres de los pueblos indígenas. .
mí corazón ♥️ y  mí #sororidad con el pueblo #pemón.
.
#repost @meridafeminista
• • • • • •
comunicado
respecto a los hechos suscitados el día 22 de febrero del 2019, la red mérida feminista repudia y lamenta el vil asesinato de zoraida rodríguez, mujer indígena, perteneciente a la comunidad kumarakapay, quién fallece por impacto de arma de fuego durante el enfrentamiento entre indígenas pertenecientes a la etnia pemón y el ejército, cuando la comunidad indígena intentaba mantener la frontera abierta para recibir la ayuda humanitaria. 
rechazamos activamente estos actos, que enmarcan la violación de derechos humanos de las mujeres y que demuestran la violencia en la que viven las mujeres venezolanas en un estado en crisis política y económica. no solo es una mujer más a la larga lista de feminicidios que se suman día a día, sino es una mujer que representa a nuestros pueblos originarios, la voz de nuestras etnias indígenas y del pueblo pemón, una voz que se ha apagado y merece justicia. 
como mujeres venezolanas y feministas, luchamos para que la violencia no nos siga arrebatando vidas. así que exigimos luz y justicia en la lamentable muerte de zoraida, así como exigimos que se esclarezcan los sucesos violentos que nos han arrebatado la vida de nuestros hermanos indígenas y agravando la compleja crisis que vive venezuela. 
a su vez, señalamos la discriminante estrategia utilizada por el estado venezolano en la ciudad fronteriza de ureña el 23 de febrero, de obstaculizar la entrada de la ayuda humanitaria extranjera utilizando como barrera a las mujeres de la policía nacional bolivariana. mujeres, que a pesar de estar preparadas para las situaciones de conflicto, serían las primeras en padecer cualquier altercado violento. 
rechazamos todos los hechos violentos que ponen en riesgo la seguridad y dignidad de las mujeres y niñas venezolanas. .
#venezuela #ddhh #feministas #metoo #niunamas #hazmejusticia #créeme #venezuela

text:
as a black woman pastor who suffered childhood sexual abuse, i never really identified with the term “survivor.” in the age of #metoo, i know this word connotes something very specific. and for all of the dialogue we’re having about healing sexual trauma, we’re still not dealing with ending male sexual violence. 😢😡
.
in an effort to heal sistas from and end sexual abuse in black religious spaces, i am proffering an online course for black women of faith who have suffered childhood sexual abuse and/or male sexual violence. 🙏🏿
.
while today is the official launch, you can begin at any time! together we will explore mindfulness, ritual, the socio-political nature of sexuality in black communities/churches, and how to begin or deepen your healing journey. 👏🏿
.
it is my prayer that every woman who takes this course is transformed into a surthrivor, and, empowered to become an anti-sexual abuse advocate within her religious community...mama audre lorde said, “the master’s tools will never dismantle the master’s house.” now is our time for shifting from silence to storytelling, so we can remove the silence, stigma, and shame attached to our trauma; and end childhood sexual abuse and male sexual violence in the black church, for good. ⛪️✊🏿
.
link in bio (and please dm me with questions!). ✌🏿💜☀️

text:
backstage post-shoot, back in my softs. 
i had a wonderful afternoon shooting with a very talented all-female crew. although i had a variety of fun outfits, i was happy to get back into my “soft clothes” and enjoy the rest of a lazy sunday. 
as a woman in the last days of her 40s, i feel more and more confident about who i am. and i hate to be trite, but i also find that i have way, way fewer f*cks to give. i have self-censored out of my own lexicon phrases like, “if it’s okay with you,” and “does that make sense,” and inserting diminishing terms like, “just” and “maybe.” i voice my opinions quickly and clearly, particularly if they are in response to unacceptable behavior. 
recently, a (male) coworker responded to my stating to another (male) coworker that, in fact, i did not need anyone to stand up and offer me their seat in the crowded room, by saying, “yeah, she’s part of me too!” in no uncertain terms and loudly enough for all to hear, i said, “that’s not funny,” and left the room. he im’d me immediately, apologizing and then came to my office to apologize in person. if i hadn’t spoken up, i’m sure it would have gone unnoticed. yet, there’s still room for improvement, because he didn’t make his apology publicly. but if next time, he thinks before he speaks, some progress has been made. 
when it comes to modeling, the same idgaf no-nonsense approach applies. “where is the camera looking right now? how close up are you? no, i don’t want to be in that pose.” all these simple boundaries, simple preferences about how my body is shown, in years past would have seemed rude of me to ask and to say. not anymore. is it the shift in hormones due to perimenopause? is it the years and years of experience giving me that much more confidence? could be both, and likely more.

text: okay, i see you all. listen, i get that you all want cooper & gaga to be together. but, let me break this down. i’m scrolling here watching the same people that post about women empowering other women, women’s rights, #metoo, and all of these other issues women deal with also making posts wanting him to leave his girlfriend & the mother of his child to be with gaga 🤦🏻‍♀️ is that what we women want as other women? you want him to leave his wife for another woman? you want gaga to be a home wrecker & take someone else’s man simply because they have good on-screen chemistry? really? that goes against everything that you have supposedly stood for. don’t be hypocritical like this. how about we root for friendship? how about we root for a good man who can have a great friendship with another woman while simultaneously being an amazing significant other?. i for one am rooting for coopers successful relationship with his girlfriend and mother of his child. i’m also rooting for gaga to continue to inspire others, to excel in her career & to find someone she loves. i hope they have created a great friendship between their families. i hope that this friendship creates another epic collaboration of both of their talents & they bless us with another amazing performance. i am rooting for them to do the right thing & show the world it’s possible❤️ #amberlynnthoughts

⠀

⠀

text_retweet:
#kalangalatoo 
#repost @nowhitesaviors with @make_repost
・・・
we need to ask, once you hear this story, where do ugandan girls fit into your #metoo and #timesup movements? it seems that much of the time, the only stories you care about spreading are those with fame, power or influence... and we know, most especially, wyt women.
•
today we are asking you to listen to the stories of countless ugandan women and girls who have endured hell at the hands of a white, belgian citizen by the name of bery glaser.
•
in 2013, mr. glaser was arrested for these same allegations, however, the girls who were living at his home “bery’s place” in kalangala - they had nowhere else to go, no way to continue paying for school fees, and so when it came time for court, they did not feel safe enough to testify.
•
this time must be different. after being arrested in 2013, mr. glaser was able to return to the home in kalangala and allegedly has continued to exploit and abuse many of the underage girls in his “care”.
•
yesterday, 24th february 2019, uganda police went to kalangala to arrest mr. glaser — he escaped, his whereabouts currently unknown, however they were able to arrest his wife.
•
we need you to share this story with the hashtag #kalangalatoo — we need to stand together to bring this man to justice.
•
we are also collecting donations to meet the immediate needs of the girls — there “support” has been taken away as of yesterday and we are asking for all to pitch in where they can to meet their immediate needs.
•
<< you can donate through our paypal or venmo — please earmark “kalangala” >> @wpi.uganda 
#kampala #beryglaser #kalangala #berysplace #endhumantrafficking #sextrafficking

i am currently writing a fantasy novel that is based on filipino folklore, mythology and legends. i have fallen head over heels over this project, loving it more than the last book i wrote. it's one of those projects you wish never will end, but i have to or else it'll never be done xd i've learnt so much about a history otherwise unknown to me.

i think it is important for this type of work to be produced. and it is being done. i'm excited to read trese, which is sort of similar vein of what i'm doing. did you know netflix is also producing it too?!!! i am so stoked. represent! i read and watched so much from the @theaswangproject in my research too, check them out!

text:
the text in this image is from rabbi adina allen of the @jewishstudioproject. she’s speaking of the work of the darshan, a creative rabbinic educator who uses popular culture to share the sacred teachings of #adonai, the god of the jews who stole themselves from #slavery. 
my mother, a jew by birth and ancestral inheritance, named me darshan for a dear friend who was a traveling musician from #india who left her homeland to spread the sacred teachings of her ancestors. original darshan as i’ve come to call her spent time in #newyork in the 1970s where she met my parents and later settled in #amsterdam where she founded a music school. her name, darshan, i was always told, mean “sacred vision” in #sanskrit and was a divine invocation common to #hindus and #buddhists. 
did my mother know its #jewish significance? my mother, so estranged from her folk for being an incest #survivor at the hands of her grandfather, was forever a curious wanderer who found faith and family among refugees, misfits, survivors. #metoo.

years ago, a jewish #israeli told me my name had religious meaning among jews. i was surprised but delighted; learned teacher was his translation. 
as a #boricuasuperjew who works for global decolonization, i have a bitter relationship with adonai. it is my most jewish trait. he loves me all the more for it and has blessed my work on #propheticeconomics and #decolonialbiznessworld. 
imagine that.
name: darshan elena campos

text:
i've yet to speak on this because i don't really have a dog in this fight but here's my two cents:

i want to make it known that if you can still support someone like vic mignogna on top of flat-out refusing to entertain the notion he might have actually done what he's been accused of and would sooner blame the women accusing him of the things he's done only trying to ruin his career just because he has a new movie out to believe he might actually be guilty after all the things that he's done over the years and continues to do to this day,you've made it significantly harder for me to trust you. i will always believe the victims over the abusers. always. besides,dozens people have been saying these things about him well before the #metoo movement ever came into existence. plus,he is no different than harvey weinstein. so i'll close with this:  i hope  he is never rehired by funimation,roosterteeth or any of his other previous employers,is forever blacklisted in the anime industry,and his reputation is forever tarnished in the public eye. i will always #standwithwomen and wholeheartedly support the #kickvic movement. if you still support him,please do me a favor and fuck off. he got what was coming to him. and i,for one,am glad he got fired. he should've learned not to be a creep and to not prey on underage girls at conventions. maybe then he'd still have his career. good riddance.

text: it is how you hold the experience not the experience itself that affects your emotions and behaviors based upon having had that experience.  what you tell yourself about a life event is more powerful than having experienced the pain of the event. do you tell yourself / or believe that you are damaged now?  are you less than others now?  are you broken?  are you unfortunate?  unlucky?  weak?  what you believe about yourself is the most powerful healing or killing tool you possess!  and you are in control of your beliefs, which are only repeated thoughts.  contact me for a friendly discussion to learn more about your personal powers.  #womensupportwomen #womeninspiringwomen #metoo #metoomovement #trauma #traumaresolution #personalempowerment #choices #healthychoices #memories #whoiam #who #selfdefined #selfdefenseforwomen #selfdevelopment #selfdestruction
