text: #donttakethispersonally #speakthetruth #antibullshit #antigossip #respresentauthenticity #metoo. speaking out against someones bullshit or hypocrisy is always hard. you get this ball of nerves and anxiety in ur stomach. your thoughts start second doubting yourself as someone doesn’t  acknowledge your point of view , the reality u see right in front of you or the feelings you express. you ask yourself why are humans not always decent to each other and why do they treat people less then they are worth. you don’t need people like that in ur life because frustrating or not, their fakeness is red flags that they are not genuine people. stick with people who appreciate you, who don’t act fake and who respect u. and keep standing up for ur values, ur beliefs, defend people who have less power in society and fight against conformity. i consider success in life to be when you learn how to be kind and open minded to people..

text: raise your hand if forgiveness has ever been pushed on you too quickly 🙋🏻‍♀️ ——————————————— i say this as a believer, and a proponent of forgiveness: forgiveness is great. it’s sacred & beautiful & other-worldly. but....please stop implying that a victim will instantaneously be healed when s/he forgives a perpetrator (if this happened to you - you’re the exception, not the rule). ☝🏼——————————————— this is victimizing the victim and spiritual bypassing, & you do not understand trauma if you start pushing forgiveness on survivors prematurely. if you did, you would not do this. 🙅🏼‍♂️——————————————— forgiveness is a deeply personal journey rather than a point of arrival. and it is beyond our ability to explain how outright damaging it is to survivors when forgiveness is prematurely expected of them. stop contributing to this narrative and recognize that people tend to come to forgiveness when they aren’t pressured, coerced, or rushed into it.

text:

never stop being a good person because of bad people. 🌻 i often hear my peers and others of my generation make statements regarding their patience with the world around them. they've been lied to too many times, betrayed, taken advantage of, taken for granted, cheated on, or hurt through out their lives and multiple times at that. the bad decisions and actions of others have caused them to close off, shut down, or keep people out. a coping mechanism. an unhealthy one.

our surroundings and experiences are what make our reality. what we think to ourselves over and over, turns into how we talk, and eventually you see action. we have bad experiences growing up, hit the rim of adulthood and have already set hard lines in the sand. and for every time someone hurts us, the lines become more defined. we must put an end to this. this is normal in society, for people across all ages. a social norm that is stunting the growth of opportunities and creativity during a time when we need it the most. we have to learn not to block others or limit our tolerance simply because the last person didn't quite fit the requirements to be in your life. please understand, there are billions of people sharing this space we call earth. everyone is not bad or out to get you. everyone has their own guidelines on what it means to be a good person and we all are mastering the skill of communicating what that is and who we are....to be continued...

never stop being a good person because of bad people. 🌻 i often hear my peers and others of my generation make statements regarding their patience with the world around them. they've been lied to too many times, betrayed, taken advantage of, taken for granted, cheated on, or hurt through out their lives and multiple times at that. the bad decisions and actions of others have caused them to close off, shut down, or keep people out. a coping mechanism. an unhealthy one.

our surroundings and experiences are what make our reality. what we think to ourselves over and over, turns into how we talk, and eventually you see action. we have bad experiences growing up, hit the rim of adulthood and have already set hard lines in the sand. and for every time someone hurts us, the lines become more defined. we must put an end to this. this is normal in society, for people across all ages. a social norm that is stunting the growth of opportunities and creativity during a time when we need it the most. we have to learn not to block others or limit our tolerance simply because the last person didn't quite fit the requirements to be in your life. please understand, there are billions of people sharing this space we call earth. everyone is not bad or out to get you. everyone has their own guidelines on what it means to be a good person and we all are mastering the skill of communicating what that is and who we are....to be continued...
.

text: in a lively talk, acclaimed public intellectual gurcharan das revealed the two secrets of happiness. first, we must love what we do, and so our choice of profession requires discovering what we are passionate about. second, the goals of our public and private lives must be in harmony. a balance must be found between duties to ourselves (kama) and duties to others (dharma). for instance, romantic monogamous love (“kama realism”) can be seen as a middle path between polygamy (“kama optimism”) and sexual renunciation (“kama pessimism”). with the triple talaq bill, decriminalization of homosexuality, the sabarimala verdict, and #metoo, the year 2018 for das marks the beginning of our emotional independence, after our political independence in 1947 and our economic independence in 1991 with liberalization.

text:
today’s the day!
•
we’ve kept our lips sealed long enough! we’re so excited to share with you all our recent feature in @yogajournal. check out the link in our bio as we chat about the highs and lows of our 20+ year friendship, the inception of on the mend, and offer some heart-opening poses for healing.
•
reminder to anyone still interested in joining us for our next california healing retreat...we are now accepting submissions through 3.2.19 for our 20% off scholarship. to enter:
👉🏻 visit the “on the mend idyllwild” link in our bio
👉🏻 join seek retreat
👉🏻 press “request booking” to apply for the retreat (no payment needed)
👉🏻 submit your response in the text box, explaining why this healing retreat is so important to you!
•
we will announce the winner on 3.4.19. we can’t wait to get to know you all more, and walk alongside you in this journey!
•
**those who have already signed up or applied for the retreat are not eligible to apply for this scholarship.

text:
what happens to a woman brain when she has been assaulted, traumatized either mentally or physically, can be seen on an mri.  yes evolutionary principles of survival protect the brain.
we treat this condition in our clinic as ptsd depression and anxiety. this is a labor of love for us, this is empowering those in our community who are good people, women and girls who merely due to their gender seem in some peoples eyes have a lower rank in our society.  nearly 5000 women will die at the hands of their intimate partner.  but many more, the majority will escape and live. with help healing takes place.  today in our clinic a lady us marine who’s head was split open is coming for daily treatments.  she has ptsd untreated for 10 years.  tms is a tool we use to rebuild the nerve pathways using neuroplasticity. #tmstherapy #batteredwomen #fear #abuse #intimatepartnerviolence #metoo #ptsd #depression #anxiety #rape #love is not enough. #rape #childabuse #veterans #intimatepartnerabuse #usatoday #mentalhealthawareness

text:
red carpet en cuatro combos💪🏻#pinkpanther #power en la gala de los #oscars 👛 del espectacular #valentino de #gemmachan al pulido diseño de #jennypackham elegido por #mariekondo (la mujer que ordena armarios y no nos deja tener más de 30 libros 👀) pasando por el homenaje a #karllagerfeld de #lisabonet y su husband (khal drogo)🌸todo un repertorio de #rosas en la #redcarpet 👄 reivindicando y reinterpretando el color tradicional femenino #metoo in #pink
💪🏻
la similitud de #looks de la chica dior #charlizetheron e #irinashayk, incluyendo el corte de pelo #bob en tono oscuro, auguran tendencia. ¿quién es quién?
💇🏻‍♀️
los hombres por fin empiezan a seguir el ejemplo de #jaredleto (dónde estabas?) y se divierten con la moda 👗 falda de #randirahm para #billyporter y #look #púrpura #prince para #spikelee (eran amigos), #adamlambert
⭐️
si la gala de los oscar es el reflejo de su tiempo, esta nos muestra el triunfo de las mujeres y de los afroamericanos, pero también de la música sobre las palabras y de la ostentación en forma de #joyas de infarto 💎 el de #ladygaga remember #audreyhepburn se lleva la palma pero también ha habido serpientes bulgari en #charlizetheron &#mileycyrus, diademas cartier... #diamondpower #oscars2019

text:
just how “famous” is this school of performing art seoul (sopa)? it is renowned for having the most idol graduates in korea.

it is highly likely that you will be able to recognize a name or several from the list of idols that have graduated, been attending or about to attend this school!

school of performing arts seoul was reportedly abused and used by the principal and his wife. in a performance in japan arranged by them, their students were made to perform sexy dance against their will and were instructed to do “skinship”. the financial support of ten million won (usd9,000) from the host in japan was paid to the wife while the students were made to cover all the expenses arising from the performance including their flight tickets to japan from their own pockets. they were suddenly notified of the performance schedule the day before and had to practice till past midnight the next day to prepare for it.

the students tried to expose this injustice on their social media but were directly threatened with charges of defamation via phone calls from the school. they were forbidden to speak about what took place at the performance and forced to face the school disciplinary committee if they tried to speak up.

for the sake of justice and to prevent similar incident from happening to other students, these brave student warriors decided to make a musical video to expose the truth of what really happened.

who is sinner _ reporting the damage and unfairness of seoul performance art high school students.

name: how can this be right?
tweet_full:
just how “famous” is this school of performing art seoul (sopa)? it is renowned for having the most idol graduates in korea.

it is highly likely that you will be able to recognize a name or several from the list of idols that have graduated, been attending or about to attend this school!

school of performing arts seoul was reportedly abused and used by the principal and his wife. in a performance in japan arranged by them, their students were made to perform sexy dance against their will and were instructed to do “skinship”. the ficial support of ten million won (usd9,000) from the host in japan was paid to the wife while the students were made to cover all the expenses arising from the performance including their flight tickets to japan from their own pockets. they were suddenly notified of the performance schedule the day before and had to practice till past midnight the next day to prepare for it.

the students tried to expose this injustice on their social media but were directly threatened with charges of defamation via phone calls from the school. they were forbidden to speak about what took place at the performance and forced to face the school disciplinary committee if they tried to speak up.

for the sake of justice and to prevent similar incident from happening to other students, these brave student warriors decided to make a musical video to expose the truth of what really happened.

who is sinner _ reporting the damage and unfairness of seoul performance art high school students.

now why tf have i spent years cringing at these texts and couldn’t think of the one statement that would communicate the nausea that these texts create, and call out the obvious intent of the repetitive texts, even though they’re not technically sayin anything “wrong” in particular...
it’s just too obvious...we see it from a mile away. (for a bit of context so fragile cis men don’t come on here with the “men can’t give compliments anymore?” spiel; save your clucking for another post). ☝🏽
this is usually coming from a dude that habitually texts you with this every other morning, but he’s not your boyfriend. in fact you have a completely platonic relationship with him and always will. but these mostly annoying reminders make you sense that he doesn’t understand this boundary and this response is a perfect way to help them understand. 
eureka! 
curve level: expert. 
taking notes 📝 📚📓🧮📊📉
#fuckboyoftheday
#fbotd

text:
the time when... everyone became a brand.... 🤳🏼🤳🏼🤳🏼
my mum came to stay with me last week, and while pushing my baby jack up harlow hill she exclaimed “have you noticed that everyone is a brand these days...?!”
😂 i answered in my most professional marketer voice “hmm yes mum that’s very topical and factually correct.”
the woman’s got a point...
if you hark back even five years ago, the only people who could market themselves as a brand were the likes of @oprah and @theellenshow so how is it that larissa at the end of the street who is no older than 16 but bloody good at putting her eye brows on just hit 5,000 followers on @instagram i hear you scream? well, its a bit more long winded than this, but in simple terms it’s down to being in 2019, where a cleverly used hashtag and a certain amount of followers attracts brands who then approach them. they are only approached if they are “on brand”. this then becomes “an influencer”. take this  cheery photo of me lurching out of a car with some roses, if @interflorauk approached me this is the sort of photo i would post with a hashtag resembling #brightenmyday 
it’s refreshing that we can all become a brand for sure, but also slightly bizarre! keen to give it a try?
1. decide what you are good at / what gets you excited? 
2. create an instagram account 
3. adopt a hashtag which you use on every post
4. identify values behind everything you post. or. creativity, honesty, humour.
5. believe in what your account stands for. 
reading list- @lindseykelk #oneinamillion

text:
📽movie scenes #5 📽
me too, 25 years back. 
watch with audio and read below.
▫️
25 years back, a gem of feminist movie was released, magalir mattum, which narrates the story of three women, satya (revathi), janaki (urvashi), papamma (rohini), working for the same fashion export company, who are harassed by a womanizer manager, pandiyan (nasser) and somehow take revenge of him. this scene is the first step of their (very comical) revenge. pandiyan blackmails them about a murder they aren't responsible for and asks them to spend all the three a night with him in his guest house. satya, janaki and papamma, decide to use this occasion to trap him in his house. 
this incredible story named "women only", just like the buses reserved for women in tamil nadu, is also a bunch of men's baby, written by my favourite crazy mohan, directed by my favourite singeetam srinivasa rao and produced by my favourite kamal haasan. but it's above all a rare feminist tamil movie carried by a trio of extraordinary actresses (i adore them since childhood). somehow, magalir mattum is the tamil ancestor of the "me too" movement. after all, papamma just summed up what victims of harassment want to say to those men : "gammu'nu kada kasmalam".
happy birthday magalir mattum ! 💕
▫️▫️▫️
▪️films : magalir mattum
▪️directors : singeetam srinivasa rao
▪️cinematography : tirru.

text:
¡hola, querubines!
por fin tengo en mis manos el ejemplar del #omgbooktour y no puedo estar más emocionada y feliz: por todos los comentarios, pegatinas y dibujos que las preciosas personitas de las cinco paradas han diseminado en su interior, sí, pero también por el cariño con el que se ha llevado a cabo el libro viajero.
gracias a @dnxspain y @delnuevoextremo por darle alas al proyecto y a vosotros y vosotras por ayudar, a través de vuestras reseñas y apoyo, a que #ohmygothess siga conquistando corazones.
os loveo.💜
os dejo las cuentas de las personas participantes en este booktour para que les echéis un vistazo, porque son maravillosas:
1. nana de @nochesleyendo 
2. ro y eli de @romanticoslibros y @librosconalma.18 (son mellis y forman un pack indivisible que adoramos).
3. clau de @claudia.blues 
4. laura de @rushreaderblog
5. tania de @taniosca
💬
espero vuestros comentarios sobre el booktour y esta pequeña parte que os muestro de él.
#pregunta
🖤 dicen por ahí algo de una lectura conjunta, ¿quién se animaría? solo os haría falta el libro y muchas ganas de fangirlear.

text:
💥💖exciting announcement💖💥
.
.
i’m so beyond excited to go back to the 
path of love retreat this april and staff it this time around!
.
i attended path of love in colorado back in september and it truely changed my life in those 7 days. you can read about my experience below.
.
this time around i get to help staff and support others in their journey and own life changing transformations! it is the most beautiful, transformational and fun week you will ever have and you make lifelong genuine and true friends 🥰
.
if anyone has interest or questions about attending, check out the following website:
https://pathretreats.com
.
or you can email the organizer for more information! 
prema@pathretreats.com
.
everybody needs to go through a path of love week sometime in their life ... men, women, all ages and every single walk of life. i can’t wait to go back and be part of this beautiful and important work. would love to see you there! 🖤🥰🙏🏽
.
.
.
“my experience”
👇🏽👇🏽👇🏽
path of love retreat
•
do you ever feel like there are distinct moments or experiences that you know for the rest of your life there is a “before that experience” and an “after that experience”??? well this was by a landslide the biggest transformational week of my life and there is a distinct before and after...
...
4 weeks ago today i left an 8 day retreat called path of love. i spent two days beforehand outside of denver in a camper trailer at the top of a mountain (with black bears roaming freely!) on someone’s plot of land in order to prepare my mind and body. 😂 you know me, i always like an adventure 😉⛰🐻
•
then i embarked on the most transformational week of my life in loveland, colorado. i didn’t know anyone. i had been eyeing this retreat for over two years. but everything and every trauma and experience led me to this moment. to this process. to the people i shared this with. this was the right time for me as life was just beginning to turn to light after an extreme dark period.
•
path of love is a holistic journey into self discoveries, insights and many many breakthroughs. it’s a personal development process based around our spirit, mind and body.
•
continued in comments

love you all ❤️

text:
i felt this sentence perfectly sums up by exhausting mind, or in fact not feeling like i have a mind at all <3 
i don't usually talk this openly about my personal situation.. but i've felt this overwhelming urge to speak out, even if i somewhat regret it later as now i feel super vulnerable.

here it goes: i have the label 'manic depressive', as scary as it sounds it simply means one day im happy, bubbly & energised yet the next i feel numb, lost and anxiously unwanted. there is no obvious trend or trigger, but i have learnt to control it... so that i can protect myself and others.

today is a tough day... not for any reason at all. despite the sun shining, despite the amazing people in my life on a daily basis i still feel an overwhelming sense of being lost, built upon more unnecessary emotions. 
i constantly say how mental health is "easier to talk about" and how "open" others are to the idea of an illness being in the mind, but yet i've never, properly, been able to write a paragraph like this about myself.

i am ok. yesterday i was great. tomorrow? i'll find out in the morning. it's bloody exhausting, but to anyone who ever feels like me, i get you, you get it and a lot of people do too. spread the love because it's not so easy to find it in yourself. 💕 #depressive #manicdepressive #mentalhealth #metoo #love #spreadlove #mind #lost #losingmymind #marktwain #quote #together #lovewins #smile

what’s in it? 
that big round thing is 1 whole egg, 138g egg whites, 28g part-skim/low moisture shredded mozzarella cheese, 1/2c broccoli that i cut up all small, and lil salt, pepper and a medley of spices to bring some heat to this breakfast partay. -
-
if you’re like me and do not endeavor in the eating of tha #meats (i do eat fish though 🐟) or do eat meat, but struggle to afford the amount necessary to achieve your daily protein goal, #eggs 🥚 are the way to go! they are a great source of protein, omega 3 fatty acids, and most importantly #affordable for all you struggling college cats out there #metoo -
-
if you’re sick and tired of eggs because you basically live off of them...like me lol, step up yo #egggame and give this simple recipe a go! 🍳😋 -
-
1. get a small pot and spray with olive oil (or a tsp of any other cooking oil)
2. turn on the lowest heat, add broccoli and cover. 
3. while the pan and broccoli begin heating, whisk together egg-whites, whole egg, cheese, and salt&pepper then add to pan immediately.
4. cover and cook on low heat for 10-15min, or until noice and fluffy 😁 -
-
tip: don’t try to rush this, unless you like wet eggs with a burnt egg crust. if you do, turn up the heat! haha.
-
-
enjoying my breakfast with refreshing ice tea lemon #aminoenergy from #womensbest
i’m not sponsored or an ambassador for this company, but i want to be honest with you and say, ladies, if you want to pick up your a-game in the gym or just life in general, @womensbest is literally the best company i’ve ever tried! i absolutely love their products!!!! i’ve tried a lot of companies in the past, but after my first purchase with them, i’ve gotten their products non-stop ever since. they just released a new flavor of “bcaa amino,” #passionmango and i’m so excited to give it a go 🤪 also, @krissycela just shared the release of her and women’s best #chocolatebrownie protein coming the 26th of this month! 💕
-
-
i hope you all enjoyed this breakfast. let me know what you think! 🌞
-
-

text:
🏆en i̇yi̇ erkek oyuncu: rami malek
2018'in en iyi performansıydı. zaten rami malek, freddie mercury karakteriyle çoktan sinema tarihine adını yazdırdı. ama akademi açısından da 'eşcinsel bir şarkıcı tiplemesi'ne ödül verdik gibi politik açıdan planlı bir hareketti. akademi'nin ezberlerinin değişmediğini, makyaj dönüşümüyle canlandırılan gerçek karakterlerin tuttuğunu bir kez daha gördük. christian bale de zaten onun esas rakibiydi ve aynı stratejiyle ilerlemişti. 🏆en i̇yi̇ kadin oyuncu: olivia colman
glenn close, richard burton ve peter o'toole ile beraber oyuncu kategorilerinde 7'den fazla adaylık alıp sıfır çeken 3 oyuncu arasına adını yazdırdı. zaten bu kategoride 70 yaşın üstünde sadece iki isim zafere ulaşmıştı, onlar da üzerinde uzlaşılan oyunculardı. katherine hepburn 74'ünde dördüncü oscar'ını almıştı, jessica tandy 80'inde çok sevilen "bayan daisy ve şoförü"nün ana figürüydü. akademi'nin bir oyuncuya ödül vermeyince onun gönlünü 'onur ödülü' ile alma geleneğine bir başka isim olarak eklendi. muhtemelen onur ödülü birkaç sene içinde gelir. biseksüel kraliçe rolünde olivia colman, #metoo dönemine uygun bir tipleme yaratarak fox searchlight'ın stratejilerini lehine çevirdi. bafta ve altın küre (komedi-müzikal) kazananıydı ve ödüle ulaştı. zaten 2007'de de marion cotillard bu istastistikle ve fransızca performansıyla yine 65 yaş üzerindeki julie christie'yi yenmişti. close-colman çekişmesinden çıkan sonuç şaşırtmadı. •
•

text:
jedna taková banalita, jo... poslední týdny ve svém těhotenském životě pozoruji takový neblahý jev, který mě donutil k úvaze. když procházím dveřma a jsem líná si je dokořán otevřít (ano, je to tak), dost často se rochnu klikou do břicha. jako žádný zranění se zatím nekonalo. vždycky si tak zabrblám, moc o tom neuvažuju a jdu dál. jako když si (u)kopnete malíček o roh skříňky nebo si dáte hlavou o digestoř. až teď mi to ale došlo!  na vině totiž není ani tak moje nešikovnost, jako spíš fakt, že můj mozek prostě dosud nezpracoval ten dmoucí pupek. jednoduše řečeno mě ještě nemá v oku. nezvykl si, že první jde břicho a pak až já. těžko tudíž může předvídat, že do skuliny, kam se cpu, se bez lehkého škobrtnutí prostě nenarvu. nevyšle mému pohybovému aparátu ten správný signál a já se pak logicky nemůžu tý klice vyhnout! děje se to taky někomu?
.
.
.

text:
humans don’t come with care instructions but maybe we should. because of the ways i’ve been hurt before, i have a hard time asking for what i need and trusting that people will take care of me without making me pay for it somehow later.

i am learning to let my guard down but i need to go at a pace that feels #safe. if you push me too hard i will #break. i can usually be put back together with some #genuine #affection. a #kind word, #gentle #touch or helping me meet my basic #needs (#food, #drink, #rest, #stretch) that i’ve probably been neglecting for too long because i’ve been #busy taking care of everyone around me. 
learning to ask for what you #need and #want can be #challenging but it’s worth it. we are worth it. 
#handlewithcare #fiercelove #worthit #metoo #selfcare #hangry #salty #growthmindset #snuggle #momsformation #iseeyou

text:
✊🏽🎬 us domestic workers are using, roma, the oscar-winning movie about rodríguez’s life as a young, indigenous housekeeper in 1970s mexico city, to educate the larger public on the issues surrounding their profession and to press for legislation that would improve their working conditions. rosa sanluis, a member of the national domestic workers alliance (ndwa), notes ,”it’s so rare to see a story or a movie about a domestic worker — i think roma makes the struggles of the domestic worker visible.”
.............
members of the @domesticworkers alliance were invited early on by producers, participant media, to see the @romacuaron movie, hold screenings, and attend the premiere at the venice film festival. “behind closed doors, we are very vulnerable to exploitation,” sanluis said.
..............
on oscar night, the alliance hosted a screening of the academy awards in los angeles with the well-known actresses and activists tarana burke, diane guerrero, rashida jones, eva longoria and olga segura. “the ndwa wanted to have that presence there so that the public and press can see that the work of domestic workers is essential in millions of homes in this country,” sanluis said.
.............
📌article: https://www.google.com/amp/s/www.nbcnews.com/news/amp/ncna974641
.............

text:
this!!! it’s a simple but effective, predictable, set up. it’s low & dirty. you get shoved out the way & then the stories get told to the child(ren). then the stupid, annoying, nonsensical questions turn to look for you. you abandoned your baby? you gave your kid away to your abuser? what real mother gives her child away to a person who is a dark, shameful, tortured soul? what mother who loves, just simply walks away? ignorance is not encouraged here but inevitable. so, yes, i am a kick ass mom. i love my daughters, fiercely! i nursed my daughters for the first year of their lives and loved being a new mom. there’s always been this very unique soul connection that ties us together. my love for my daughters is geographically agnostic. i was a young, happy, care free, single mom, who was raised by wolves. yeah, some of the unfortunate events got the worst of me and it stung bad for some time. but i wasn’t about to be labeled weak, nor a bad mom & have that resonate. i stood up for myself. i accepted my wrongs. i started working excruciatingly hard on my life. soulwork that has taken years. most people experience parent alienation through a break up or divorce. not me. i didn’t get that far. i was brave enough and god trusting enough @ 24, to accept a pregnancy & have a daughter from an abuser, who i fell into a dark, sespool toxic, isolated, nightmare with. i was indifferent to life, newly divorced, in fact, from a mechanically arranged marriage & single mom of 2 beautiful girls, 5 & 3 yrs old. i was in over my head & completely isolated from everyone & everything i knew. i believe in doing what’s right, even when it’s easy to do a wrong. i may have been a weak, broken, abused, woman...but all that... & rape & pregnancy, do not have to be your story or your child’s. i’m still in the, in between, of the journey, but experiencing what god is doing, i know there is redemption, restoration thru gods love, grace, forgiveness & so much more! 
i’m writing the story of-for, aaliyah iris. 
yeshua, is the lover of my soul & everything else! i’ve been blessed ridiculously in this life considering the hand dealt. i owe & give all the glory to my lord and savior jesus christ!

text:
(2/2) "i saw my play performed in english… and all of a sudden, i discovered a whole new world… a whole new me – in another language. so i decided to stay in the us and continue to write my plays – then screenplays – in english. next year, i moved to new york to study at nyu.
sometimes i wonder what would have happened if i went back to russia that summer… would i be a different person? would i be telling different stories? i can’t even imagine what my life would be like… it’s one of these decisions that made me what i am." marina shron in her latest interview with native influence. read the full version here: http://ow.ly/gids30nk58y

text: the studio wyse team just wrapped their fourth issue of ryerson university magazine, a publication that connects alumni, donors, staff, and students to the inspiring stories coming out of the school. this issue's highlights include: toronto's new wave of diy filmmakers, photographed by carlos osorio; chiara ghigliazza illustrating on the topic of #metoo; sandy nicholson photographs an aerospace engineering professor working to improve airline cabins. for more on this project and others from rgd members, check out our latest project showcase at rgd.ca #design #graphicdesign #rgdprojectshowcase #magazinedesign #editorialdesign #printdesign #designproject #designprocess #designinspiration @studiowyse

text_retweet:
thank you @gaysifamily
#repost @gaysifamily
• • • • •
c for consent : navigating intimacy in queer relationships
.
.
in 2006, tarana burke, an african-american civil rights activist from new york began using the phrase “me too” as an effort to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society. eleven years later, in the wake of allegations against harvey weinstein, the phrase was morphed into a hashtag by american actress alyssa milano. what began as an effort to simply “give people a sense of the magnitude of the problem,” went on to become a space where women could finally open up about their worst experiences. late last year, when former actress tanushree dutta accused nana patekar of sexual harassment, it set into motion the “me too” movement in india. without taking away what the movement has achieved, we must acknowledge that it comes with its own share of hang ups. take for example, the fact that the movement does not give space to the 600,000 women in india who are currently involuntary sex workers, and are typically poor, uneducated or lack a family. several dalit feminist activists spoke up about how the movement was not accessible to dalit women, especially considering that the movement repeatedly called the losha a “witch hunt.”
.
.
but, did you ever wonder why there were no stories by lesbians or transwomen? data suggests that approximately 1 in 8 lesbian women and nearly half of bisexual women experience rape in their lifetime, and nearly half of bisexual men and four in ten gay men have experienced sexual violence other than rape in their lifetime. transgender individuals are most affected by  hate-based violence, and about  64% of  them have experienced sexual assault in their lifetime. it is also important to point out this statistics have been provided by the cdc and there isn’t enough information about the same within indian context. given the fact that until recently homosexuality was a crime, intra-community sexual assault continues to go unreported and unacknowledged. (full article on gaysi website).
.
.
#india #metoo #lgbtqi #queer #consent #metooindia #gender #sexuality #survey
.
.
artwork by @shubhshree_math

text:
おはよう
朝食　豆乳＋納豆＋シラス＋ねぎ＋卵

昨日は、チートデイ🎵とても楽しい一日でした。

大好きなお店ばかり😄ストーリーにあげてないものも、唐揚げ　ケーキ二つ。
ということで
体重は……55.9キロ
１キロちょっとね増加。
糖質も必要な栄養　全くのとらないのでなくて、とり過ぎない。
糖質が必要な時もありますよ😁糖質は、色んな食材に入ってます。
必ず、『○○○　糖質』と検索しましょう。成分表はチェック忘れずに。
糖類０ってなってても、糖質は０ではないですよ。
糖類にも、色々あります。

diet　とは、食習慣、食生活　
体重の変化でなくて…生活習慣を見直して、健康的に、自分が好きな自分になろう。
たまには、不健康な事😅も　これまた　楽しいストレス解消。

昨日、post　ストーリー　したお店から、イイね　お礼のdm ストーリー　ありました。
大好きなお店ばかりだったので、本当に嬉しかったです。

これからも、行きます。応援します。
よろしくお願いします。

@fullfullvillage 明太フランスno.1
@chiffoncakemarie シフォンケーキ種類の多さにびっくり
@caffarel_hy チョコレート大好き
@pgm_0610 610　いちごパフェ　エリザベスは、3月10日までだよ。

@sou_611_ souのカトルカール　美味しかった。まじ美味しかった。

ウーパンベーカリー　はちみつバター　久しぶりに食べた。運良く、並んでなくて、ゆっくり選べた　美味しかった。

トミのタコ焼きも久しぶりに、美味しかった。

福津市あんずのお肉の工場直販所にも行けたし……お肉安くて美味しいよ。

よー食べました。

さぁ、今週はどうなるでしょう。
今日も一日頑張りましょう。

‪looking into the prospects of dismantling status quo and preconceived notions of what it means to be a desi girl. what is she, a feminazi, a godawful western propaganda?! uff, besharam.‬ 🤭 navigating through feminism in pakistan and amplifying the conversation in the face of stigma is misunderstood at best and ridiculed at worst. but despite it all, being radical to me is fighting the good fight. to speak the uncomfortable truth and not soften for their egos. to recenter righteous and political anger, to call an act of crime by its name, to support minorities and put money where my mouth is. to recognize my privilege, reflect and unlearn my own internalized bias. to understand the pain of my sisters who face the burnt of early marriages and honor violence in this day and age. to honor the resilience and resistance, by keeping it real.

the idea was prompted by @getradicalpk. it’s refreshing to have a pakistani brand amalgamating art & activism. they’re a cause based clothing line, and share profits with local artisans and charities.

text: i haven't shared my story in detail anywhere (except to mike) and it's been 17 years. i have been struggling really badly with flashbacks lately and a couple of times, it became paralyzing. on a cold fall night during my first year at odu, i was visiting an apartment with friends where i took these shots with vodka & hot sauce in them - which i remember thinking was so weird because it cancelled out the sting of the hot sauce & the bitterness of the vodka and they really weren't so bad. a boy at the party kept walking by me & repeatedly pinching me on my arms, i guess it was flirting? it really hurt & i just laughed it off because i had no concept of sticking up for myself back then. i was an insecure & broken version of myself having just escaped a life back home of perpetual arguing & alcoholism, but like many people who leave a crappy situation & haven't dealt with what was experienced - you aren't thinking clearly so you're almost certain you'll feel less pain if you jump into a different kind of pain. so, binge drinking & bad decisions it was. except i know i wasn't drinking enough to have blacked out that night...yet i wake up on a couch in a house i don't recognize. it was not the place we originally were. but i recognized the person i was with. the one who had aggressively flirted with me earlier. next thing i know i'm on the floor & i don't think i need to say more. i remember looking at the ceiling, crying, i remember seeing people do drugs off of a table in the next room while fear & loathing in las vegas played on the tv. i remember stepping outside and realizing i was on the same street as my dorm, so i walked home with my arms covered in huge bruises and my soul covered in shame and disgust. i carried that shame for months and for years. i let that shame hurt others, i got really, really, really lost for a long time. when mike finally came into my life, i found my safe haven. (continued in comments)

text:
‘to be a man’: a portrait series challenging the concept of toxic masculinity.
.
steven. belgium. “it’s okay not to embody what society defines a ‘real man’ to be. there is an all encompassing structure surrounding what being a ‘real man’ is all about. it dictates everything from a man’s behaviour and posture to the way a man should walk, even to the way a man should dance. i definitely don’t dance like a real man. it goes as far as having your legs crossed while sitting, the way to treat women, friends… the way to treat everything around you. it pushes your ego and testosterone above everything else.”
- see www.jessicaamity.com for the full series! .
.
.

text:
the flood-affected districts of kerala are now on the road to recovery. with the loss of livelihood, property and many more things, the scars that are left behind and not only physical but emotional too.

but what was even more concerning were the incidences of substance abuse, sexual abuse and a dip in the academic performances of children. 
world vision india is now providing psychosocial intervention in communities and schools affected by the floods. so far, a total of 1390 children in veliyanad and kainankary panchayaths of alappuzha district, have been covered under this intervention.

text:
〰 to do list 〰
chaque semaine, nous faisons notre sélection des trucs cool à faire, une sortie culturelle, un super film au ciné, un resto qui vient d'ouvrir, pleins de trucs "frais-ministes" et "frais-minins" !
.
👉 tous les mois (commencez dès aujourd'hui d'ailleurs) : vous pensiez avoir votre podcast préféré, c'était avant de connaitre @abientotdeterevoir by @sophiemarielarrouy !! elle invite chaque mois une personnalité pour parler de sa life et de ce qu'il aime (ou pas), c'est des barres de rire (même avec benoit hamon). bonne écoute !
👉 tous les soirs à partir de 18h : direction @combat.belleville un bar à cocktail créé et tenu par des nanas. margot lecarpentier avec elena schmitt, ont ouvert un bar à cocktails 100 % féminin l’année de l’affaire weinstein et de #metoo. on y est allée la semaine passé, c'est une tuerie !
👉 jeudi 28 à 18h30 : l'asso @asterya.eu et @les_explo vous invite au @lehasardludique pour parler de sexualité positive et répondre à ces questions essentielles : comment pouvons-nous donc agir pour promouvoir une éducation sexuelle plus positive, et de quoi devrait-elle être faite ? viens avec avec tes idées, questions et/ou expériences pour changer notre façon de voir la sexualité !
👉 vendredi à 19h : le label d'événements pop meufs lance sont mois de festival valorisant la place des femmes dans la société au @lepavillondescanaux . et vendredi, la revue orbs lance son "spécial féminin" avec la rencontre de l'équipe, dédicaces, librairie et "corner" orbs + djset "déesse, femme et nature" avec eric van hoecke à partir de 21h30. fiestaaaaa !
👉 dimanche à partir de 14h30 : @feministsofparis vous emmène sur les traces du féminisme à travers les ruelles du quartier-village de la butte-aux-cailles, haut lieu du street-art féministe. découvrez ensemble l'histoire du quartier, du mouvement pour l"égalité entre les genre, et celle de d'artistes femmes et/ou féministes dans une ambiance conviviale d'échanges et de débats. .
tous les liens sont dispos dans notre bio ✌
.
.
#todolist #todo #bonsplans #femmessingulieres #metoo #streetart #popmeufs #sexualitepositive #bar # paris #quoifaireaparis #feminisme

text:
namn✏️: sture nilsson
-
fysisk beskrivning💪🏼: smal och elegant kropp, ben som ätpinnar, två emaljögon.
-
bakgrund📋: sture bor i en lägenhet i hägerstensåsen med sin gamla kollega harry. han beskriver sig själv som en nyfiken extrovert med starka, välinformerade politiska åsikter. sture pratar åtta språk flytande och jobbar deltid på el giganten i södertälje.
.
ibland kan stures beteende uppfattas som gränslöst och få honom att hamna i knepiga situationer. på en charterresa till turkiet var flygplanet tvungen att nödlanda efter flera kvinnliga passagerare klagade på att sture hade slickat på deras näsborrar när de vilade. ’blötfoder är min favorit’ sa sture när han försvarade sig själv under rättegången. ”
.
när sture avtjänade sitt straff för sexuell trakassering i ett fängelse i södra turkiet blev han radikaliserad av islamiska staten, och snart efter han släpptes smugglades sture över gränsen till syrien. hans starka retorik och lång militärerfarenhet ledde till att sture snabbt blev chef av kalifatens kattdivision, och han hamnade högst upp på usa:s most wanted lista efter han livesändes en halshuggning på en vithövdad havsörn på facebook.
.
när is började förlora kriget bestämde sture sig att åka hem till sverige på en enhjuling. en dag, när han tiggde på liljeholmstorget, adopterades han av ett vackert men naivt par. han fortsätter kampen mot västvärlden med fokus på hägerstens invånare, och använder sig av etablerade tortyrmetoder såsom sömnbrist och att bajsa i blomkrukor.
.
hkb betyg: 10/10 🐈
.

text:
institutional betrayal
is rampant 
in response to sexual assault, harassment, and violence. *

it is the advisor 
who tells you not to come forward 
and ruin the reputation *

of a fine faculty member, *
or  their contributions to a discipline *
it is the nurse that questions
 if you really said no, 
or the judiciary that says 
you misunderstood, 
it wasn’t that bad. 
you are the only one.

the titleix officer who says
it was meant as a complement
this isn’t serious enough
you are both to blame
*
if you knew then 
what you know now, 
what would you warn femme folx about on your campus?

this week we are exploring institutional betrayal. 
share with us.

text: #kairedcarpet #kaiawardsseason #oscar #oscars #oscars2019 think pink...มาช้าหน่อย เพราะติดภารกิจ แต่ที่แน่ๆ ที่ถูกพูดถึงมากที่สุด ก็คือ เทรนด์สีชมพูบนพรมแดงออสการ์ที่มาให้เห็นตั้งแต่เริ่มยันจบงาน เด่นสุดยกให้ @gemma_chan ที่ใจกล้าลาก @maisonvalentino กูตูร์สีชมพูมาใส่เรียลเวย์ให้เห็นในความใจกล้า ชมพูคราวนี้มาพร้อมกับหลากเทคนิคตั้งแต่ระบาย อัดพลีท จับเดรป ถามว่าทำไมต้องชมพู เราว่ามันคือต่อเนื่องมาจากกระแส #metoo เมื่อสองปีที่ผ่านมานั่นแหละ แต่ปีนี้มันถูกลดระดับเหลือแต่การใช้สีเป็นสัญลักษณ์ แถมมันยังดูสดใสไร้มลพิษ แบบสีกลางๆ ที่ดูสวยสมหญิง โดยไม่ต้องกรีดร้องอะไรให้มากความนั่นเอง

swipe 👉 #rkelly another #sextape found! | being turned over to police today | lawyer states their is a 3rd tape also!
.
prosecutors are about to get another sex tape in the r. kelly case today and sources say it is even more shocking than the most recent one.

sources familiar with the case say attorney michael avenatti will turn over a 55-minute vhs video monday to cook county prosecutors. we're told the video shows r. kelly having sex with the same 14-year-old girl depicted in the first video avenatti obtained, which was shot in 1999. this second video was shot around 2000.

just like the first video, there are multiple references to the girl being 14 years old. our sources say r. kelly is repeatedly "coaching" the girl through various sexual situations.

at one point r. kelly is seen choking the girl while having anal intercourse. our sources also say there's a part where he takes some sort of lotion and "sprays" it all over her face. we're told he then chokes her, mounts her from behind and turns her face to a camera for a reaction shot.

we've also learned avenatti is in the process of procuring a 3rd tape showing r. kelly with a different girl who at the time was somewhere between 13 and 16 years old. our sources say avenatti's team has identified the person in possession of the video and is attempting to get it.

text:
once a month a group of kick-ass, real, honest and a little bit mad women get together to unpick, unravel, question, reflect upon, learn and rewrite their stories (with a table full of food always!) we all come from different background and have different stories that have bought us together. but we all sit with and listen to each other’s journeys, hold space and find ways of changing the narrative.
a few years ago being so vulnerable, sharing so honestly and even being able to hear truths would have had me running for the hills.
yet this new way of being and living has opened up the world in ways i could never imagine and it’s a blessed place to be.
#womentogether #truthtopower #holdingspace #unravel #rewriteyourstory #spring #metoo #muslimmetoo #sisterhood #soulfood

text:
i invite all readers to peruse seyed ahmad alhassan's explanation of this subject thouthfully and deeply, because he has responded to all the controversies surrounding the issue of the polygamy of the messenger of allah (pbuh).
in this regard,  he(pbuh) stated that: "but the issue of marriage at the time of the messenger of allah, mohammad (pbuh), and especially in the conditions of his life, even before islam, there were also numerous marriages, because of the increasing proportion of women to #men , and as it is clear that in order to solve this problem, there was  no acceptable social solution except polygamy. 
the reason why there was such a problem at that time was that there were constant wars and raids,
and this always let lots of men to be killed; while women stayed home and did not routinely go out and no danger threatened them, they were even captured and not killed like men in the wars. 
this increase in the number of women in those living conditions was such a social problem that many women who did not find a husband would raise flags for declaring their tendency to have sex with men, and #women who had red flags were famous in the society. 
many men killed their daughters in their infancy, a phenomenon that was known as burying-girls-alive, and the cause of this phenomenon was the increase in the number of women, most of whom did not achieve husbands, in the community and tended to have sexual relationships without a social law (like marriage). (facebook official page, 23/06/2013) * read the whole article in the site.
http://www.almahdyoon.org
#women_in_the_divine_governmen

text:
c for consent : navigating intimacy in queer relationships
.
.
in 2006, tarana burke, an african-american civil rights activist from new york began using the phrase “me too” as an effort to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society. eleven years later, in the wake of allegations against harvey weinstein, the phrase was morphed into a hashtag by american actress alyssa milano. what began as an effort to simply “give people a sense of the magnitude of the problem,” went on to become a space where women could finally open up about their worst experiences. late last year, when former actress tanushree dutta accused nana patekar of sexual harassment, it set into motion the “me too” movement in india. without taking away what the movement has achieved, we must acknowledge that it comes with its own share of hang ups. take for example, the fact that the movement does not give space to the 600,000 women in india who are currently involuntary sex workers, and are typically poor, uneducated or lack a family. several dalit feminist activists spoke up about how the movement was not accessible to dalit women, especially considering that the movement repeatedly called the losha a “witch hunt.”
.
.
but, did you ever wonder why there were no stories by lesbians or transwomen? data suggests that approximately 1 in 8 lesbian women and nearly half of bisexual women experience rape in their lifetime, and nearly half of bisexual men and four in ten gay men have experienced sexual violence other than rape in their lifetime. transgender individuals are most affected by  hate-based violence, and about  64% of  them have experienced sexual assault in their lifetime. it is also important to point out this statistics have been provided by the cdc and there isn’t enough information about the same within indian context. given the fact that until recently homosexuality was a crime, intra-community sexual assault continues to go unreported and unacknowledged. (full article on gaysi website).
.
.
#india #metoo #lgbtqi #queer #consent #metooindia #gender #sexuality #survey
.
.

text:
missing these mountains, trails, language, and people ♥️ thoughts i remember having as i paused to snap this photo back in 2016..
📷 
spending time in a developing country is a strong reminder that the things we value in western culture are often unimportant. .
while it’s vital to be aware of your surroundings in any country, when running in most areas of the united states i generally feel comfortable. on warm days i wear a sports bra and spandex shorts, and never think twice about it. aside from the occasional rude honk, or lewd comment hollered our an open window, no one bothers me. and while the stated actions cause me discomfort, they’ve never inspired fear for my safety.
.
women in guatemala, as well as other areas of central america, experience high rates of gender motivated violence. culturally, it’s not appropriate to dress in tight clothing, or expose skin, no matter the temperature.☀️ .
in a phenomenon called feminicide, a woman could be targeted in a rural community if she chose to go for a run wearing typical running gear (not that most of them have time for leisure activities anyway, as they’re typically caring for multiple children, cooking, and running a household, many before they’ve turned 18). a culture of machismo, or patriarchal dominance, has normalized violence against women. after the murder of a woman, police frequently do not search for the murderer, due to the belief that she likely did something to bring this upon herself.
.
for reference, according to amnesty international there were 670 cases of femicide in 2016, which increased to 711 cases in 2017. from my understanding, the dreaded “caravan” of immigrants that headed to the us border in late 2018 consisted primarily of young women fleeing from fear of femicide in el salvador, honduras, and guatemala.
.
how privileged am i, to be able to take travel, take photos, and then go home to a place where i know i’m safe? to a middle class (by american standards) supportive home, where i always had parents that supported my personal and academic dreams, and pushed me to be a better version of myself? and then, to be able to run out the door in my sports bra, without a worry in the world.

text:
does #oscars fashion still matter? movie award shows used to be the place where a year’s most impactful celebrity fashion statements were made and monetised. it was normal for fashion fans to sit down in front of a tv and watch the red carpet pre-show and the ceremony itself, and then tune in again a day later for a #fashion recap. but that was before the fragmentation of media, the rise of instagram and the decline of #hollywood.

while many women’s lifestyle websites still rush to publish near-identical slideshows of celebrities, hoping their round-ups will rank higher in google search results or on facebook feeds than their competitors, people who are interested in the clothes are often better off going straight to instagram, where a handy algorithm pushes the photos straight to the top anyways.

and then, there’s the question of how brands continue to fit into the red-carpet media scrum when actresses are increasingly using award shows for statements on social justice, not fashion. though the #metoo #timesup black dress movement was short lived, the labels that will be most successful on the red carpet will mostly likely adopt, not run from, social statements.

so what about you: are you still interested in seeing what celebrities are wearing on the red carpet? [link in bio] 📷: @gettyimages

text:
lisez la critique complète, ici ⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️⠀
·⠀
en sortant de la salle, je me suis précipité sur imdb pour vérifier si un film de françois ozon m'avait déjà autant enthousiasmé. force est de constater que non. d'une actualité brulante (un carton nous rappelle que le jugement du procès barbarin a lieu trois semaines après la sortie du film), c'est le sujet qui malmène ozon, l'amenant à se dépasser et à délaisser tout maniérisme agaçant ou référence encombrante à hitchcock ou fassbinder. car si ozon se voit comme un post-moderne fringant, il se révèle avant tout un des scénaristes français les plus étincelants de son temps.⠀
⠀
il est commun de reprocher aux films tirés d'histoires vraies de trop coller aux faits. or, si le réalisateur respecte scrupuleusement ces derniers, c'est leur subtil agencement au sein d'une structure admirable de limpidité qui vient à la fois faire sens et provoquer l'émotion. "je ne vais pas y aller par quatre chemins" assène le personnage de melvil poupaud en guise d'introduction, une phrase qu'ozon pourrait aisément reprendre à son compte. il ne s'embarrasse pas d'introduire la réalité du trauma et de la pédophilie dans un quotidien. l'état de fait est déjà là, à la vue de tous, juste non-adressé (ce qui se vérifie en permanence depuis #metoo). c'est le vrai sujet du film : la libération de la parole. ses mécanismes, ses causes, ses conséquences. en scénariste averti, ozon creuse consciencieusement son sujet, n'oublie rien, pas même les dérives (le personnage de ménochet, en pleine expédition punitive, ne manque pas d'être agaçant) et pose une question fondamentale, pourtant peu abordée : qu'est-ce que ça veut dire, être une "victime" ?⠀
⠀
on pourrait reprocher au film quelques flash-backs un peu pompiers ? pécadille, tant on jubile de voir l'éternel sale gosse du cinéma français, maintenant cinquantenaire, s'était soudainement décidé à retirer les gants de boxe pour jouer du stradivarius. comme si toute sa carrière avait abouti à ce film qui accomplit le rare exploit d'être à la fois utile, magistral et bouleversant.⠀
-⠀

text:
buchpräsentation museum folkwang, 
buchhandlung walther könig, museumsplatz 1 
do, 28. 2., 18 uhr
merlijn schoonenboom: was ist schön? wie unser geschmack sich wandelt. „ein kluges buch das ich mit gewinn gelesen habe.“
philipp demandt, direktor städel museum, frankfurt

wer entscheidet, was kunst oder kitsch ist? wie groß ist der einfluss des kunstmarkts und was hat politische ideologie damit zu tun? am anfang von merlijn schoonenbooms überlegungen zur geschichte des geschmacks steht ein gemälde des salonmalers william adolphe bouguereau nymphe et satyre (1873). wie kann ein bild, das erst als kunst bejubelt dann als kitsch verurteilt wurde, heute wieder salonfähig sein? anhand dieses umstrittenen gemäldes folgt schoonenboom auf seiner reise von paris nach new york über rotterdam, wien und berlin der frage, was geschmack ausmacht vom modernismus bis zur #metoo-bewegung. der autor lebt und arbeitet in berlin. sein buch wurde in den niederlanden für den jan hanlo essay-preis nominiert.
moderation: ulrich fernkorn

text:
this month we will have the pleasure of hosting a discussion on the issue of women's rights between rozana isa, executive director of sister in islam forum, and @annececilemailfert , founder of the foundation of women "fondation des femmes". this french talk will be moderated by @tini_ariffin, former host of 3r (respek, relaks, respon) who has spearheaded numerous digital media projects in the area of young women empowerment.

the speakers, both experienced activists, will share their experiences in advocating women's rights in malaysia and france and reflect on the way ahead for us: what methods can be used most effectively to advocate women's rights today? in the light of the recent #metoo movement and its ripples worldwide, to what extent are women's rights to be understood universally or adapted to specific cultural contexts? how much progress still needs to be done to ensure equal rights between men and women ?

rsvp at www.alliancefrancaise.org.my

organised by
embassy of france in malaysia
alliance française de kuala lumpur ------------------------------------------------------- what is french talks?

welcoming french and malaysian experts, it aims at creating a space of dialogue, and a bridge between the two countries and their cultures. this is particularly timely in this new malaysia where people are willing to express their views

text:
prosecutors are about to get another sex tape in the r. kelly case and sources say it is even more shocking than the most recent one.

sources familiar with the case say attorney michael avenatti will turn over a 55-minute vhs video monday to cook county prosecutors. we're told the video shows r. kelly having sex with the same 14-year-old girl depicted in the first video avenatti obtained, which was shot in 1999. this second video was shot around 2000.

just like the first video, there are multiple references to the girl being 14 years old. our sources say r. kelly is repeatedly "coaching" the girl through various sexual situations.

at one point r. kelly is seen choking the girl while having anal intercourse. our sources also say there's a part where he takes some sort of lotion and "sprays" it all over her face. we're told he then chokes her, mounts her from behind and turns her face to a camera for a reaction shot.

we've also learned avenatti is in the process of procuring a 3rd tape showing r. kelly with a different girl who at the time was somewhere between 13 and 16 years old. our sources say avenatti's team has identified the person in possession of the video and is attempting to get it.

text: #nathaliesimard , une magnifique femme inspirante qui a donné une voix à ceux qui n’en ont pas. les agressions sexuelles sont  encore trop souvent un tabou. avec son livre , madame simard lève le voile sur les sévices corporels, psychologiques et sexuels qu’elle a vécu entre les griffes de l’homme qui prétendait l’aimer. pour moi, la lecture de son récit a marqué le début de ma propre reconstruction. cela m’a a permis de réaliser que je n’étais pas seule mais surtout, que moi aussi, je pouvais me battre contre mes démons.ces ordures ne méritent par que l’on souffre pour eux; ils n’en valent pas la peine.  parce que enfin, nous osons dénoncer et parce que non, nous ne resterons pas victimes toute notre vie. parce que la souffrance qu'ils m'ont causée me sert à présent de moteur pour avancer dans la vie. parce que au lieu de me détruire comme ils le souhaitaient, ils ont activé ma rage et ma soif de vivre. et parce que pour moi, le dessin est mon moyen d'expression. et parce que nous sommes des survivantes avec une vie et un bel avenir devant nous ( contrairement à vous qui aviez besoin de nous agresser pour vous remonter!). merci pour ton courage et ton implication. ‪#moiaussi‬ ‪#metoo‬ ‪#ellesaussi‬ ‪#noustoutes‬ #victime #survivor #wrestler #combattant #agression ‪#stopagresseurs‬#moiaussi #metoo #stop #enough #music #bookstagram #noviolenceagainstwomen #femme #rdi #strongwomen #superwoman #strength #bestrong #courage #artistsoninstagram #art #bookstagram #love

text: i'm an independent, stubborn woman  who does not need a man but still, i prefer a gentleman who can take care of me, worship the ground i walk in, ravage me in bed and put me into place once in a while. i love seeing him watch me move mountain as i make room for him in my life. and yes, i might be high maintenance at times but that's just because i can sustain myself. every tangible thing a man can give, i can give myself. so my definition  of spoiling is giving me your time. give me experience.

text:
in conjunction with international women's day on the 9th of march 2019, there will be a march in kl and kk - #womensmarchmy - for women's rights and human rights of other marginalized communities in malaysia.

leading up to this march, #womensmarchmy festival was held yesterday to educate and expand the collective understanding of the demands for this year's march. there was a movie screening and a series of thought-provoking discussions on many significant issues and topics. among them were "the power of rallying & rallying collective power", "eliminating gender-based violence & its root causes", "equal pay, access & recognition of work", "redefining masculinity in the age of #metoo". some of the speakers were jac sm kee, gisele rimong, subatra jayaraj, zurairi ar, rizal rozhan, dorian wilde and many more.

this year's demands are some of the most basic and fundamental rights and prerogative that we should have as human beings and it's unbelievable that we are still demanding for it in 2019. if you feel the same way, walk in solidarity at #womensmarchmy on 9.3.2019!

#womensmarchmy is coordinated by a loose coalition comprising various actors including collectives, non-governmental organisations and individuals.

for more details: https://womensmarchmy.wordpress.com/

text:
at the age of 14 nick olivas had sex with a 20 year old woman who had taken his vulnerability at the time as an advantage, this was in the state of arizona where the legal age of consent is 15 meaning nick was underage and having sexual relations with a 20 year old should’ve resulted in jail time for the woman. and these sexual relations weren’t consensual, he was taken advantage of so this wold be a child rape case, nick hadn’t pressed charges on her though. he didn’t realise he could at the time. nick and the woman went their seperate ways and he lived a relatively normal life, until he got sent papers from the state demanding her paid child support. she was 6 years of age and nick had no clue she even existed until now, he owed them $15,000 for child support and medical bills and $380 a month for a child that was conceived of rape and he had no clue even existed. have you heard of this on the news? have you heard of it being widely talked about? there was a similar case that happened much much longer ago, this one happened around 2014 i believe but was barely spoken about, this isn’t at all acceptable and this is extremely disgusting and disturbing. we hear more about women rape victims and how they deal with these issues but we barely here about the men rape victims. we barely hear about female rapists, enough is enough.

text:
recently i had to let go of some things...somethings that’s had a hold on me for years.  it’s funny...sometimes we don’t know the things that hold us back or keep us from being our best selves but then one day we wake up and we decide we want more.  i use to feel guilty for wanting more, for having more, for being more, for knowing i could be better...it’s what kept me always settling for something small.  i use to tell myself that was me being humble, that was me being a realist, but in reality that was me playing it safe.  it’s not wrong to want more for your life, to want better people around you, or to stop settling for people that make you feel you have to earn their allegiance or love.  truth is we deserve more...way more than we can imagine.  and that’s not selfish or conceited or anything like that...that just makes us right and in harmony with what we deserve...the best.  and maybe we’ll have to let some things go or even some people...cuz we gotta make room for bigger and better...even if it’s scary...or unfamiliar....or even uncomfortable.  welcome to the world you’ve never known. the world you’ve always deserved...the world you’re absolutely worthy to have.  #youareenough
.
.

text:
selbstverteidigung (wteo) - schulen für avci wing tsun & avci escrima
19. februar 2019 ·

die schulleiter der schulen borken, düsseldorf und borken (wteo) führen mit dauerhaftem lehrauftrag auch für die ausländerbehörde borken sicherheitsschulungen durch.
gelegentlich veröffentlichen wir die ein oder andere impression und eine information zum status quo.

am 19.02.2019 referierte sifu david kropfgans wieder für das ordnungsamt im kreis borken zum thema "selbstschutz" (avci system). das "avci system" ist ein speziell auf behördliche bedürfnisse abgestimmtes technikprogramm, welches vom verbandsleiter der wteo, meister salih avci, entwickelt wurde. "avci system" unterliegt durch eine jahrelange, enge zusammenarbeit der wteo mit ordnungsbehördlichen fortbildern einer ständigen evaluierung. es ist ein lebendes system.

offensichtlich sprechen sich die referenzen unserer schulen und die anwendbarkeit des „avci-systems“ in den kommunalen ordnungsbehörden herum.
im rahmen von sichtungsverfahren konnten wir bereits in mehreren behörden und unternehmen durch professionalität überzeugen.

wir bedanken uns beim kreis borken für das vertrauen und die zusammenarbeit, sowie bei meister salih avci für die vorarbeit. wir werden unser bestmögliches dazu beitragen, damit auch die borkener mitarbeiter gesund wieder nach hause kommen.

lars kirz
david kropfgans

text:
📸📸📸
from ➡️ @moodymixologist 
s u n s e t  s t r i p
.
i have tons of drinks bookmarked on @diffordsguide (i’m sure you can relate!) and each week i’m trying to go through and choose something fun and different to try.
.
this one caught my eye as it was recommended to shake rather than stir the ingredients for extra dilution and aeration. the original is nice, but i found it a bit sweet for my taste. i made my own interpretation by replacing half of the aperol with bitter bianco and i cut the grapefruit liqueur down to a 1/2 oz. the original is garnished with an orange twist, so i took the opportunity to try a new design 🌿
.
original recipe via @diffordsguide:
1.5 oz bourbon
1 oz aperol
1 oz pamplemousse rose liqueur
-shaken rather than stirred, for more dilution and aeration.

text:
me too: year two

who: emily steel, sohaila abdulali, tina tchen

hosted by lenore taylor

a decade since the me too campaign began, and a year since #metoo rocked the entertainment industry, there has been a clear cultural shift. across industries, women who were preyed upon, exploited and harassed have spoken out and sought justice, and the movement has gone global.

but it hasn't all happened smoothly. louis ck returned to the comedy stage. the senate confirmed brett kavanaugh to the supreme court. now that accountability frameworks have been put in place, are the structures of justice and legal systems changing? have we seen a fundamental shift in the way power functions, or is it temporary and superficial? how is #metoo playing out in different countries and cultures?

in this essential panel, we'll be exploring how the movement must evolve to represent women worldwide, and to create long-lasting cultural and political change.

keen to know more? to book your spot for this live stream event 
search 'women' at www.midcoastlibraries.com.au/events
#allaboutwomen #midcoastlibraries #nswpubliclibraries #librariesofinstagram
